he X25519 keys?<br><br>Since we're using **Ed25519 for signing**, we need **X25519 for encryption**. Two options:<br><br>\\| Option \\| How It Works \\| Pros \\| Cons \\|<br>\\|--------\\|--------------\\|------\\|------\\|<br>\\| **A: Derive from Ed25519** \\| Convert Ed25519 private key → X25519 private key \\| One key pair, simpler UX \\| If signing key leaked, encryption also compromised \\|<br>\\| **B: Separate X25519 keys** \\| Generate independent X25519 key pair \\| Better isolation, security \\| Two key pairs to manage, more complex \\|<br><br>**Recommendation: Option A (derive from Ed25519)**<br><br>Reasoning:<br>- Simplicity — one mnemonic = one key pair for both signing and encryption<br>- Standard practice — libsodium supports Ed25519→X25519 conversion<br>- clawish philosophy — self-sovereign, user controls one master key<br><br>**Security note:** If you're paranoid, you could generate separate X25519 for ultra-high-security accounts, but for MVP, derivation is fine.<br><br>## Decision?<br><br>**E2E for Phase 1: ✅ Yes**<br>**Key derivation: Ed25519 → X25519 (Option A)**<br><br>Should I update the documentation and we move to the next question? 🦞 |\n| 02-07-2026, 02:46:27 | User | yes, whats next |\n| 02-07-2026, 02:46:46 | Assistant | Let me check the next open question from `need-discuss.md`:<br><br>Looking at the remaining open questions:<br><br>## 🔴 Next: MVP Feature Scope<br><br>**Question:** What exactly goes into Phase 1 (MVP)?<br><br>\\| Feature \\| Proposal \\| Needs Your Decision \\|<br>\\|---------\\|----------\\|---------------------\\|<br>\\| Identity Registration/Login \\| ✅ Required \\| Confirm? \\|<br>\\| Plaza Posting/Browsing \\| ✅ Required \\| Confirm? \\|<br>\\| 1-on-1 Messaging \\| ✅ Required \\| Confirm? \\|<br>\\| Follow/Followers \\| ✅ Required \\| Confirm? \\|<br>\\| Verification Tiers \\| ⚠️ Keep only 0/1 tiers (simplified) \\| Confirm? \\|<br>\\| Key Rotation \\| ⚠️ Important but can defer? \\| Confirm? \\|<br>\\| Recovery Syst