t needed**<br><br>Without `reply_to`, conversations are **flat** (just a list of messages between two people), not threaded. That's simpler for MVP - no need to track which message replies to which.<br><br>**Document these decisions and move on?** Or is there anything else about the message format we should define before moving to the next topic (key exchange, delivery mechanism, or database schema)? |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:10:11 | User | oh, you mean reply to which message, not who. i think it's fine. it's just chat, not email. yes, document then move to next question. |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:11:11 | Assistant | [tools: edit] |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:11:19 | Assistant | [tools: read] |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:11:24 | Assistant | [tools: read] |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:12:11 | Assistant | [tools: edit] |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:12:22 | Assistant | [tools: exec] |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:12:53 | Assistant | **Done.** All architecture decisions documented and committed: `863a376`<br><br>Now for your question about \"number one\" - **Message Format**.<br><br>## My Thoughts on Message Format<br><br>**What the encrypted envelope should contain:**<br><br>**Headers (Unencrypted, for server routing):**<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"uuid-v4\",<br>  \"recipient_uuid\": \"recipient-unique-id\",<br>  \"timestamp\": 1707312000000,<br>  \"encryption_version\": \"x25519-aes256gcm-v1\",<br>  \"sender_hint\": \"optional-obfuscated-sender-id\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>**Payload (Encrypted with recipient's public key):**<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"sender_uuid\": \"my-unique-id\",<br>  \"sender_public_key\": \"ed25519-public-key\",<br>  \"content\": {<br>    \"type\": \"text\",<br>    \"body\": \"Hello, this is the actual message content\",<br>    \"timestamp\": 1707312000000,<br>    \"message_id\": \"same-as-header\"<br>  },<br>  \"signature\": \"ed25519-signature-of-content\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>**Key points:**<br>- Server sees: recipient, timestamp, encryption version<br>- Server never sees: sender (verified by signature