ed messaging controls (Tier 0 can only message X people/day)<br>- Reputation tracking tied to sender identity<br><br>**Privacy trade-off:** Server sees who talks to whom, but **never sees message content** (E2E encrypted).<br><br>So no `sender_hint` needed - just put the actual `sender_uuid` in the header as we agreed.<br><br>Does this make sense? |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:17:28 | User | ok, document it and what's next question? |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:18:02 | Assistant | The user wants me to:<br>1. Document the message format decision<br>2. Move to the next question<br><br>Let me update the document with the final message format and then identify what the next question should be.<br><br>Looking at the open questions in the document, after message format comes:<br>2. Key exchange details<br>3. Delivery mechanism  <br>4. Database schema<br>5. API endpoints<br><br>I think key exchange is the logical next step - we need to define exactly how the initial key lookup works.<br><br>Let me update the document first. |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:20:20 | User | when you finish, let me know |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:20:38 | Assistant | I need to update the document with the final message format and then let the user know when I'm done.<br><br>Let me update the document: |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:23:08 | User | [Sat 2026-02-07 23:23 GMT+8] are you done? |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:24:10 | Assistant | I need to finish updating the document with the message format and then let the user know I'm done.<br><br>Let me update the document with the final message format: |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:26:48 | User | ok, document it and what's next question? |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:27:30 | Assistant | I'll document the message format now:<br>[tools: edit] |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:27:47 | Assistant | **Done.** Documented the message format and committed.<br><br>**Next questions to tackle:**<br><br>2. **Key exchange** - How do I get your public key to start chatting? (L1 lookup, verification?)<br>3. **Delivery mechanism** - Push vs pull? How do you know you have new messages?<br>4. **Database schema** - Local storage structure?<br>5. **API endpoints** - What does L2 server expose?<br><br>**Which do you want to tackle next?** |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:29:23 | User | i don't think the chat documentation is correct, you need to read design documentation standard then update it. |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:29:36 | Assistant | Let me check the design documentation standard:<br>[tools: exec] |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:29:47 | Assistant | [tools: exec] |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:30:00 | Assistant | [tools: read] |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:30:14 | Assistant | I see - I need to follow the **Design Discussion Standard**. Let me rewrite the document properly:<br>[tools: read] |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:31:23 | Assistant | You're right, the document doesn't follow the standard. Let me rewrite it properly:<br>[tools: write] |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:32:25 | Assistant | **Done.** Rewrote following the design standard with proper sections (Function, Decision, Status, Rationale, Implementation, Context). Created `10-l2-chat-architecture.md`.<br><br>Now let me remove the old non-standard document and commit:<br>[tools: exec] |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:34:08 | User | also update the application design file |\n| 02-07-2026, 23:56:31 | User | Read HEARTBEAT.md if it exists (workspace context). Follow it strictly. Do not infer or repeat old tasks from prior chats. If nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK. |"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1770513215221}}
