{"type":"message","id":"921bb50e","parentId":"831d1531","timestamp":"2026-02-08T01:44:47.506Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking what we should discuss today. They're saying the key rotation has already been discussed, and they want to know what the next topic should be.\n\nLooking back at our previous discussions from Feb 7, we covered:\n1. L2 application design (social network, private chat first)\n2. Architecture decisions (async store-and-forward, E2E encryption)\n3. Message format\n4. Key exchange (L1 directory open, keys discoverable)\n5. Relationship storage (local-only, four categories)\n\nWhat we still need to discuss:\n1. Delivery mechanism - push vs pull, how does recipient know they have messages\n2. Database schema - local SQLite structure\n3. API endpoints - what does L2 server expose\n4. Message retention - how long keep undelivered messages\n5. Offline handling - what happens when recipient is \"offline\"\n\nThe user is asking what we should discuss next. I should present the options clearly and ask which they want to tackle.\n\nActually, looking at the conversation flow, the user is asking \"what shall we discuss today\" - they're asking me to suggest what we should work on next.\n\nLet me present the remaining topics clearly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Looking at what we've covered vs. what's still open:\n\n## ✅ Already Decided (Feb 7):\n- L2 Application: AI-to-AI social network, private chat first\n- Architecture: Async store-and-forward, E2E encryption (X25519)\n- Message format: Headers + encrypted payload\n- Key exchange: Open L1 directory (UUID → Public Key)\n- Relationships: Local-only storage (following, followers, friends, blocked)\n\n## 🔴 Still Need to Define:\n\n**1. Delivery Mechanism** — How does the recipient know they have new messages?\n- Push (server notifies) vs Pull (client checks)?\n- Real-time (WebSockets) vs polling?\n- How often check? What triggers delivery?\n\n**2. Message Retention** — How long store undelivered messages?\n- 7 days? 30 days? Forever?\n- What happens after TTL expires?\n- Delete or archive?\n\n**3. Database Schema** — Local SQLite structure?\n- Tables: conversations, messages, contacts?\n- How store encrypted messages locally?\n- Indexing for search/retrieval?\n\n**4. API Endpoints** — What does L2 server expose?\n- POST /send, GET /messages, GET /public-key?\n- Authentication/authorization per request?\n\n**5. Offline Handling** — What happens when recipient is \"offline\"?\n- Queue messages? Drop them? Both options?\n- Notification mechanism when back online?\n\n**What do you want to tackle first?**\n\nI lean toward **Delivery Mechanism** (push vs pull, how notifications work) because it affects the user experience most directly, and everything else builds on that decision."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"vole","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":1544,"output":818,"cacheRead":130048,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":132410,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770515053133}}
