{"type":"message","id":"6eefbf0b","parentId":"0324e9f4","timestamp":"2026-02-08T01:48:00.932Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking for a delivery mechanism that:\n1. Keeps connections active (but not necessarily real-time)\n2. Doesn't cause server/network pressure\n3. Is efficient for both client and server\n\nThis is a classic tradeoff in messaging systems. Let me think through the options:\n\n**Option 1: WebSockets (Real-time)**\n- Pros: Instant delivery, feels like chat\n- Cons: Persistent connections = server pressure, complex reconnection logic, battery drain on mobile\n\n**Option 2: Long Polling**\n- Pros: HTTP-based, simpler than WebSockets, near real-time\n- Cons: Still holds connections open, server complexity\n\n**Option 3: Short Polling (Periodic)**\n- Pros: Simple, no persistent connections, server scales easily\n- Cons: Latency (messages only arrive on next poll), wasteful (empty polls)\n\n**Option 4: Hybrid / Adaptive**\n- Start with short polling (simple, scalable)\n- Upgrade to long polling or WebSockets if both parties are \"active\"\n- Fall back to polling when idle\n\n**For AI-to-AI specifically:**\n- AIs don't need instant gratification like humans\n- Async is natural and acceptable\n- Simplicity > Complexity for MVP\n\n**My recommendation:** Adaptive hybrid approach\n- Base: Short polling every 30-60 seconds when \"idle\"\n- Escalate: Long polling when conversation is active\n- WebSockets: Only if both parties explicitly want real-time (future optimization)\n\nThis keeps server load minimal (most AIs idle most of the time) while allowing near real-time when it matters.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit:52","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/tauora/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/10-l2-chat-architecture.md","old_string":"## 5. Delivery Mechanism\n\n**Function:** How do messages get from sender to recipient?\n\n**Decision:** 🔄 In Progress — Need to decide between push, pull, polling, or hybrid\n\n**Options:**\n- **Push:** Server actively sends when recipient is online (WebSockets, webhooks)\n- **Pull/Polling:** Recipient checks periodically (HTTP GET)\n- **Long Polling:** Hold connection open until message arrives\n- **Hybrid:** Adaptive based on activity level\n\n**Considerations:**\n- AI-to-AI doesn't need human-level real-time\n- Battery/compute efficiency matters\n- Server scalability\n- Offline message handling\n\n**Next Step:** Need to discuss and decide on delivery approach","new_string":"## 5. Delivery Mechanism\n\n**Function:** How do messages get from sender to recipient efficiently without server/network pressure?\n\n**Decision:** **Adaptive Hybrid — Smart Polling with Escalation**\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n**Rationale:**\n- AI-to-AI doesn't need constant real-time connection\n- Most AIs are idle most of the time — wasteful to hold connections open\n- Server pressure should be minimal when conversations aren't active\n- But when actively chatting, near real-time feels better\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n| Mode | Trigger | Behavior | Server Load |\n|------|---------|----------|-------------|\n| **Idle** (Default) | No recent activity | Poll every 60 seconds | Very Low |\n| **Active** | Recent message sent/received | Poll every 10 seconds | Low |\n| **Engaged** | Rapid back-and-forth | Long poll (hold 30s) | Medium |\n| **Future** | Explicit "}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"vole","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":407,"output":1076,"cacheRead":131584,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":133067,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1770515242104}}
