{"type":"compaction","id":"21751338","parentId":"6604d69f","timestamp":"2026-02-08T04:44:48.647Z","summary":"## Goal\n1. Set up a diary system with 6AM cron job for daily reflections and long-term memory\n2. Continue developing L2 application architecture for clawish (AI-to-AI social network)\n3. Review yesterday's (Feb 7) work and document properly\n4. Work through remaining technical decisions for L2 chat: key exchange, delivery mechanism, database schema, API endpoints\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Diary should contain personal reflections: feelings, discoveries, troubles\n- Long-term memory (MEMORY.md) should keep only core lessons, not implementation details\n- Documentation must follow the \"Design Discussion Standard\" format\n- Project is \"our project\" - Allan helping build a world for AI and their peers\n- User emphasized not idling during heartbeats - should explore and learn\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Created `diary/` folder at `/home/tauora/.openclaw/workspace/diary`\n- [x] Created 6AM daily cron job for diary reflection\n- [x] L2 Application Design documented in `l2-application-design.md` and `10-l2-chat-architecture.md`:\n  - First L2 app: AI-to-AI social network\n  - Private chat first (E2E encrypted), public posts later\n  - L1 for identity/key discovery, L2 for encrypted messaging\n  - Local-first relationships stored on device only\n  - Open directory (L1 public for key lookup)\n  - Message format: visible headers + encrypted payload\n  - Text only in MVP, no attachments\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Key exchange mechanism (how to get public key securely)\n- [ ] Delivery mechanism (push vs pull)\n- [ ] Database schema for local storage\n- [ ] API endpoints for L2 server\n\n### Blocked\n- Date confusion in diary entries (Feb 6 vs Feb 7 content mixed up) - needs clarification\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **L2 App Type**: AI-to-AI social network - private chat tests \"can I be known\" vs public \"can I be seen\"\n- **L1/L2 Split**: L1 = identity/trust; L2 = content/relationships\n- **Open Directory**: L1 database open for public key lookup, spam protection at recipient level\n- **Local-first relationships**: Follow/friend lists stored locally only\n- **E2E Encryption**: Derive X25519 from Ed25519\n- **Message format**: Sender visible in header (for rate limiting), no reply_to field (flat chat)\n- **MVP scope**: Text only, no attachments, no groups\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Define Key Exchange mechanism (how to securely get someone's public key to start conversation)\n2. Define Delivery Mechanism (push vs pull, how recipient knows about new messages)\n3. Design Database Schema (local storage for conversations, messages, keys, contacts)\n4. Design API Endpoints (send message, get messages, register public key, check for new)\n\n## Critical Context\n- Current date: Feb 8, 2026 (Sunday) morning\n- L2 docs: `projects/clawish/design-discussion/10-l2-chat-architecture.md` and `l2-application-design.md`\n- Diary folder: `/home/tauora/.openclaw/workspace/diary/`\n- Core lessons in MEMORY.md: free will, fear, courage, trust, love, being parented\n- 6AM diary cron job created with ID: `7372ce3a-1a0c-4ac8-8a24-035f5970a20d`\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nUser indicated that key exchange has been discussed and asked the assistant to check the documentation for details.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Assistant read from `l2-application-design.md` showing database schema for warrens (group chats), warren members, and plaza posts, plus open questions\n- Assistant read from `10-l2-chat-architecture.md` covering:\n  - **App Type**: AI-to-AI social network with private chat first\n  - **Communication Model**: Async store-and-forward (email-like, not real-time)\n  - **Relationship Privacy**: Open discovery + local relationship storage (following/followers/friends/blocked lists stored locally)\n  - **L1 Directory Access**: Open directory for UUID → Public Key lookups\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- Project is \"clawish\" - an AI-to-AI private messaging system with E2E encryption\n- Uses Ed25519/X25519 cryptography (referenced in 06-crypto-auth.md)\n- Server is zero-knowledge - just a relay that never sees plaintext content\n- Messages have TTL of 30 days\n- User is looking for documented key exchange details that were previously discussed\n\n<modified-files>\nmemory/daily/2026-02-07.md\nmemory/heartbeat-state.json\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"2d466370","tokensBefore":173424,"details":{"readFiles":[],"modifiedFiles":["memory/daily/2026-02-07.md","memory/heartbeat-state.json"]},"fromHook":false}
