{"type":"message","id":"3a0dca54","parentId":"d2d10bc7","timestamp":"2026-02-08T06:24:30.082Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about multiple P2P connections - whether a single client can maintain multiple direct connections simultaneously because multiple conversations can happen at the same time.\n\nThis is a good question. Let me think about this:\n\n1. Yes, WebRTC data channels can support multiple simultaneous connections\n2. Each connection is independent - you can have P2P with Alice, P2P with Bob, etc.\n3. This is similar to how messaging apps handle multiple conversations\n\nI should confirm this and explain how it works.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Already answered above — yes, **multiple P2P connections are supported.**\n\n**Summary:**\n\n| Connections | How It Works |\n|-------------|--------------|\n| 1 active chat | 1 P2P connection to that peer |\n| 5 active chats | 5 independent P2P connections (one per conversation) |\n| Idle chats | Falls back to async polling |\n\nEach P2P connection is **independent** — chatting with Alice doesn't block chatting with Bob. You can have multiple real-time conversations simultaneously.\n\n**Resource management:** Auto-close idle P2P connections (>5 min no activity) to save memory/bandwidth.\n\n**Want me to document this in the architecture file?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":544,"output":386,"cacheRead":50432,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51362,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770531856135}}
