{"type":"message","id":"6c81a622","parentId":"810755c0","timestamp":"2026-02-08T06:30:34.101Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the first edit worked. Now I need to update the code sample and any other references to 60 seconds / 60000ms to 5 minutes / 300000ms.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"6a4ca94c-c266-45fe-b646-9236d67ba95d","name":"edit","arguments":{"newText":"```javascript\n// Client-side state machine\nfunction checkConnectionState() {\n  const timeSinceLastMessage = Date.now() - lastMessageTime;\n  \n  if (timeSinceLastMessage < 300000 && hasP2PConnection()) {  // 5 minutes = 300,000 ms\n    // Other party responded within 5 min, they're online\n    return 'P2P_REALTIME';  // Send directly\n  } else {\n    // No recent response, switch to async\n    return 'ASYNC_POLLING';  // Poll every 60s\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Why 5 Minutes Instead of 1 Minute:**\n\nFrom user experience perspective, 1 minute is too short — people need time to think, look things up, or step away briefly. Frequent reconnections during natural pauses feel disruptive.\n\n**5 minutes** gives enough buffer for:\n- Thinking about a reply\n- Looking up information\n- Brief interruptions (phone call, doorbell)\n- Natural conversation pauses\n\nIf no message for 5 minutes, or P2P connection breaks, fall back to **async polling**.","oldText":"```javascript\n// Client-side state machine\nfunction checkConnectionState() {\n  const timeSinceLastMessage = Date.now() - lastMessageTime;\n  \n  if (timeSinceLastMessage < 60000 && hasP2PConnection()) {\n    // Other party responded within 60s, they're online\n    return 'P2P_REALTIME';  // Send directly\n  } else {\n    // No recent response, switch to async\n    return 'ASYNC_POLLING';  // Poll every 60s\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Why 2 States Instead of 3:**\n\nFrom human perspective, if you receive a message back within **60 seconds**, the conversation already feels real-time. You know the other party is online. This is the trigger to create a **direct P2P connection** (WebRTC data channel).\n\nIf no message for 60 seconds, or P2P connection breaks, fall back to **async polling**.","path":"/home/tauora/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/10-l2-chat-architecture.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":819,"output":548,"cacheRead":51776,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53143,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1770532206165}}
