{"type":"message","id":"d58ce686","parentId":"d751a454","timestamp":"2026-02-08T06:35:39.265Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, now let me ask about any remaining questions for the delivery mechanism:\n\n1. **P2P signaling** - How exactly do clients establish WebRTC connection? Do they need a TURN server for NAT traversal?\n\n2. **P2P failure fallback** - What if P2P fails (NAT/firewall blocks it)? Do we need server relay as fallback?\n\n3. **Message queueing during transition** - What happens to messages sent while switching from async to P2P? Do they get duplicated?\n\n4. **Offline handling** - When recipient is completely offline (not polling at all), how long do we store messages?\n\nLet me ask these questions.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**Done!** Documented multiple P2P connections.\n\n**Commit:** `b0208fc`\n\n---\n\n**My questions about delivery mechanism:**\n\n1. **P2P Signaling** — How do clients establish the WebRTC connection? Do we need a **TURN/STUN server** for NAT traversal? Or just use L2 server for signaling?\n\n2. **P2P Failure Fallback** — What if P2P fails (firewall/NAT blocks it)? Do we:\n   - Fall back to server-relayed messages (like WhatsApp)?\n   - Just stay in async polling mode?\n\n3. **Message Queueing During Transition** — When switching from async → P2P:\n   - What happens to messages still on server?\n   - Do we fetch them first, then switch to P2P?\n   - Risk of duplication?\n\n4. **Offline Handling** — When recipient is completely offline (not polling):\n   - How long do we keep messages? (7 days? 30 days? Forever?)\n   - TTL for undelivered messages?\n\n**Which of these should we tackle?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":1694,"output":520,"cacheRead":53888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56102,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp"