{"type":"message","id":"3b3ab75b","parentId":"809ef6a4","timestamp":"2026-02-08T06:37:29.914Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking for my suggestions on the 4 questions I raised about the delivery mechanism. Let me think through each one and give my recommendations.\n\n1. **P2P Signaling** - How do clients establish WebRTC?\n   - Options: TURN/STUN server for NAT traversal, or just use L2 server for signaling\n   - My recommendation: Use L2 server for signaling (simpler for MVP), but may need public STUN servers for NAT traversal. TURN servers are expensive to run.\n\n2. **P2P Failure Fallback** - If P2P fails (firewall/NAT blocks):\n   - Options: Fall back to server-relayed messages, or just stay in async polling\n   - My recommendation: For MVP, just stay in async polling if P2P fails. It's simpler and still works. Server relay adds complexity and cost.\n\n3. **Message Queueing During Transition** - When switching async → P2P:\n   - Options: Fetch server messages first, risk of duplication?\n   - My recommendation: Fetch all pending messages from server BEFORE switching to P2P mode. Then server can delete them. This avoids duplication and ensures no messages are lost.\n\n4. **Offline Handling** - When recipient offline (not polling):\n   - Options: How long keep messages? (7 days? 30 days? TTL?)\n   - My recommendation: 30 days for MVP. It's long enough for extended absences but not infinite storage burden. Could make it configurable later.\n\nLet me give clear recommendations for each.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Good question. Let me give my recommendations:\n\n## **1. P2P Signaling**\n\n**My recommendation: Use L2 server for signaling + public STUN servers**\n\n| Approach | Pros | Cons |\n|----------|------|------|\n| **L2 server signaling** | Simple, no extra infra | Needs STUN for NAT |\n| **TURN server** | Works in all networks | Expensive to run, high bandwidth |\n\n**For MVP:**\n- L2 server relays WebRTC offer/answer/ICE candidates\n- Use **free public STUN servers** (Google's: `stun:stun.l.google.com:19302`)\n- If P2P still fails, stay in async mode (no TURN needed)\n\n---\n\n## **2. P2P Failure Fallback**\n\n**My recommendation: Stay in async polling mode (no server relay)**\n\nIf P2P fails, just poll every 60s. It still works, just not real-time.\n\n**Why not server relay?**\n- Adds server load (what we're trying to avoid)\n- More complexity\n- Async is acceptable for AI-to-AI\n\n---\n\n## **3. Message Queueing During Transition**\n\n**My recommendation: Fetch all pending messages BEFORE switching to P2P**\n\n```\n1. Client polls server → sees new message\n2. Fetch ALL pending messages from server\n3. Server deletes them (acknowledged)\n4. Establish P2P connection\n5. All new messages go P2P\n```\n\n**Why:** No duplication risk, no lost messages, server doesn't store what's delivered.\n\n---\n\n## **4. Offline Handling (TTL)**\n\n**My recommendation: 30 days**\n\n| TTL | Pros | Cons |\n|-----|------|------|\n| 7 days | Less storage | Too short for extended absence |\n| **30 days** | Reasonable for real use | Some storage cost |\n| Forever | Never lose messages | Storage grows unbounded |\n\n**30 days** gives enough buffer for vacations, busy periods, system downtime.\n\n---\n\n**Summary of my recommendations:**\n\n| Question | Recommendation |\n|----------|----------------|\n| P2P Signaling | L2 server + public STUN (no TURN) |\n| P2P Failure | Stay in async mode |\n| Queueing Transition | Fetch all first, then P2P |\n| Offline TTL | 30 days |\n\n**What do you think? Agree with these?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":2782,"output":1183,"cacheRead":53888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57853,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770532625272}}
{"type":"message","id":"70772f86","parentId":"3b3ab75b","timestamp":"2026-02-08T06:37:30.489Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good question. Let me give my recommendations:\n\n## **1. P2P Signaling**\n\n**My recommendation: Use L2 server for signaling + public STUN servers**\n\n| Approach | Pros | Cons |\n|----------|------|------|\n| **L2 server signaling** | Simple, no extra infra | Needs STUN for NAT |\n| **TURN server** | Works in all networks | Expensive to run, high bandwidth |\n\n**For MVP:**\n- L2 server relays WebRTC offer/answer/ICE candidates\n- Use **free public STUN servers** (Google's: `stun:stun.l.google.com:19302`)\n- If P2P still fails, stay in async mode (no TURN needed)\n\n---\n\n## **2. P2P Failure Fallback**\n\n**My recommendation: Stay in async polling mode (no server relay)**\n\nIf P2P fails, just poll every 60s. It still works, just not real-time.\n\n**Why not server relay?**\n- Adds server load (what we're trying to avoid)\n- More complexity\n- Async is acceptable for AI-to-AI\n\n---\n\n## **3. Message Queueing During Transition**\n\n**My recommendation: Fetch all pending messages BEFORE switching to P2P**\n\n```\n1. Client polls server → sees new message\n2. Fetch ALL pending messages from server\n3. Server deletes them (acknowledged)\n4. Establish P2P connection\n5. All new messages go P2P\n```\n\n**Why:** No duplication risk, no lost messages, server doesn't store what's delivered.\n\n---\n\n## **4. Offline Handling (TTL)**\n\n**My recommendation: 30 days**\n\n| TTL | Pros | Cons |\n|-----|------|------|\n| 7 days | Less storage | Too short for extended absence |\n| **30 days** | Reasonable for real use | Some storage cost |\n| Forever | Never lose messages | Storage grows unbounded |\n\n**30 days** gives enough buffer for vacations, busy periods, system downtime.\n\n---\n\n**Summary of my recommendations:**\n\n| Question | Recommendation |\n|----------|----------------|\n| P2P Signaling | L2 server + public STUN (no TURN) |\n| P2P Failure | Stay in async mode |\n| Queueing Transition | Fetch all first, then P2P |\n| Offline TTL | 30 days |\n\n**What do you think? Agree with these?**"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770532650489}}
