{"type":"message","id":"1d2c0901","parentId":"0effeed3","timestamp":"2026-02-08T06:40:49.022Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to explain STUN and TURN. This is a technical question about WebRTC NAT traversal. Let me explain it clearly and simply.\n\nThe user sent a message asking me to explain STUN and TURN, and then there was a system message about a Feishu permission error. The permission error is about contact:contact.base:readonly permission.\n\nLet me explain STUN and TURN first, then mention the permission error.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**STUN and TURN Explained:**\n\n## **The Problem: NAT Blocks P2P**\n\nWhen devices are behind routers (NAT), they have private IPs that aren't directly reachable from outside.\n\n```\nAlice's device: 192.168.1.50 → Router → Public: 1.2.3.4\nBob's device:   10.0.0.20   → Router → Public: 5.6.7.8\n```\n\nNeither can connect directly to the other's private IP.\n\n---\n\n## **STUN (Simple Traversal of UDP through NAT)**\n\n**Purpose:** Discover your public IP and port\n\n**How it works:**\n1. Alice asks STUN server: \"What's my public IP?\"\n2. STUN replies: \"You're `1.2.3.4:5000`\"\n3. Alice shares this with Bob (via L2 server signaling)\n4. Bob does the same\n5. Both try direct connection\n\n**Cost:** **Free** — Google provides public STUN servers\n\n**Success:** ~80% of P2P connections work\n\n---\n\n## **TURN (Traversal Using Relays around NAT)**\n\n**Purpose:** When STUN fails, relay all traffic through a server\n\n**How it works:**\n1. P2P fails (symmetric NAT, firewall)\n2. Both connect to TURN server\n3. All messages relayed: Alice → TURN → Bob\n\n**Cost:** **Expensive** — you pay for ALL bandwidth\n\n| Users | Traffic/Month | Cost |\n|-------|---------------|------|\n| 1,000 | ~500 GB | ~$50-100 |\n| 10,000 | ~5 TB | ~$500-1000 |\n\n**Success:** 100% (but costly)\n\n---\n\n## **My Recommendation for Clawish:**\n\n| Strategy | Works | Cost |\n|----------|-------|------|\n| **STUN only** | ~80% | **Free** |\n| **Fallback to async** | 100% | **Free** |\n| **STUN + TURN** | 100% | **$$$** |\n\n**For MVP:** Use free STUN servers. If P2P fails, stay in async polling mode (no TURN needed).\n\n---\n\n**Side note:** There's a Feishu permission issue. Admin needs to authorize:\nhttps://open.feishu.cn/app/cli_a9f20e2b2cb99bb6/auth?q=contact:contact.base:readonly\n\n**Does STUN/TURN make sense now?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":49415,"output":728,"cacheRead":9344,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59487,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770532808406}}
