{"type":"message","id":"51d6532a","parentId":"43ed8a72","timestamp":"2026-02-08T06:50:42.138Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about the automatic signaling process. They want to confirm:\n\n1. If user receives message within 5 minutes (we changed from 1 minute to 5 minutes)\n2. Then automatically start signaling to establish P2P\n3. Signaling success leads to P2P connection\n\nThey're asking me to confirm if this is automatic and how it works.\n\nLet me clarify the flow and confirm.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Yes, exactly! **Automatic signaling flow:**\n\n```\n1. Alice sends message via L2 server (async mode)\n   ↓\n2. Bob polls, receives message within 5 min\n   ↓\n3. Bob's client detects: \"Message received! Other party might be online\"\n   ↓\n4. Bob's client automatically:\n   - Queries STUN for public IP\n   - Sends WebRTC offer to Alice (via L2 server)\n   ↓\n5. Alice's client (still polling) receives offer\n   ↓\n6. Alice's client automatically:\n   - Queries STUN for her IP\n   - Creates WebRTC answer\n   - Sends back to Bob (via L2 server)\n   ↓\n7. Both sides exchange ICE candidates\n   ↓\n8. P2P connection established! 🎉\n   ↓\n9. All future messages flow directly (no server)\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Automatic Client Logic**\n\n```javascript\nclass ChatClient {\n  onMessageReceived(message, senderUuid) {\n    this.lastMessageTime = Date.now();\n    \n    // Auto-trigger P2P if not already connected\n    if (!this.hasP2PConnection(senderUuid)) {\n      this.initiateP2P(senderUuid);  // Automatic!\n    }\n  }\n  \n  async initiateP2P(peerUuid) {\n    // 1. Get public IP from STUN\n    const myPublicIP = await STUN.getPublicIP();\n    \n    // 2. Create WebRTC offer\n    const offer = await WebRTC.createOffer();\n    \n    // 3. Send signaling message via L2 server\n    await L2Server.send({\n      to: peerUuid,\n      type: 'webrtc_offer',\n      sdp: offer,\n      ice_candidates: [myPublicIP]\n    });\n    \n    // 4. Wait for answer (via polling)\n    // 5. Complete handshake automatically\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **User Experience**\n\n| What Happens | User Sees |\n|--------------|-----------|\n| First message | Sent via server (async) |\n| Reply received | Automatically switches to P2P |\n| P2P established | Real-time chat (no UI change) |\n| P2P fails | Stays in async (still works) |\n\n**Completely automatic.** User doesn't need to do anything.\n\n---\n\n**Your message got cut off at \"Signaling succes...\"** — what were you asking about success/failure cases?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":4258,"output":697,"cacheRead":56640,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61595,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770533416480}}
{"type":"message","id":"2c22b73a","parentId":"51d6532a","timestamp":"2026-02-08T06:50:42.235Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Queued messages while agent was busy]\n\n---\nQueued #1\n[Feishu ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75 2026-02-08 14:50 GMT+8] ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75: Okay, so it's automatically done right? If user receive message within one minute. Then automatically Start signaling request to establish p2p. Signaling success, then establish p2p. Then keep the connection for five minutes. If within five minutes there is no message or Connection break, They switch back to async. Is this the process?\n[message_id: om_x100b57b76c9204a4b27d461268b511b]"}],"timestamp":1770533442230}}
{"type":"message","id":"c6be59c5","parentId":"2c22b73a","timestamp":"2026-02-08T06:51:01.005Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking to confirm the automatic signaling and connection process. They want to verify that:\n\n1. If user receives message within 5 minutes (they said \"one minute\" but we changed it to 5 minutes)\n2. Automatically start signaling request to establish P2P\n3. Signaling success → establish P2P\n4. Keep connection for 5 minutes\n5. If no message within 5 minutes OR connection breaks → switch back to async\n\nThis is exactly the process we designed. Let me confirm this and clarify the flow.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**Yes, exactly!** You've got it right. Here's the confirmed process:\n\n## **Automatic Connection Flow**\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  ASYNC MODE (Default)                                   │\n│  • Poll every 60 seconds                                │\n│  • Messages via L2 server                               │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                         │\n                         ▼\n         Message received within 5 minutes?\n                         │\n                    YES  │\n                         ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  SIGNALING PHASE                                        │\n│  • Both clients query STUN for public IP               │\n│  • Exchange WebRTC offer/answer via L2 server          │\n│  • ~1-3 seconds                                         │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                         │\n                         ▼\n              Signaling success?\n                    /       \\\n                  YES        NO\n                   │          │\n                   ▼          ▼\n┌──────────────────────┐    Stay in async\n│  P2P MODE            │    (still works)\n│  • Direct connection │\n│  • Real-time chat    │\n│  • Keep for 5 min    │\n└──────────────────────┘\n          │\n          ▼\n    No message for 5 min\n    OR connection broken?\n          │\n         YES\n          │\n          ▼\n    Switch back to async\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Timeline Example**\n\n| Time | Event | Mode |\n|------|-------|------|\n| 0:00 | Alice sends message to Bob | Async |\n| 0:30 | Bob polls, receives message | Async → Signaling |\n| 0:32 | P2P established | P2P |\n| 0:32 - 5:00 | Chatting in real-time | P2P |\n| 5:00 | Last message sent | P2P (still active) |\n| 10:00 | No messages for 5 min | Switch to Async |\n| 10:00+ | Polling every 60s | Async |\n\n---\n\n## **Key Points**\n\n| Aspect | Behavior |\n|--------|----------|\n| **Trigger** | Message received within **5 min** (not 1 min) |\n| **Signaling** | Automatic, via L2 server |\n| **P2P duration** | **5 min** timeout (no messages = close) |\n| **Fallback** | Automatic (client detects, no user action) |\n| **User sees** | Nothing — just works |\n\n---\n\n**This is exactly the process.** Should I document this flow in the architecture file?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":728,"output":821,"cacheRead":60864,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62413,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770533442232}}
