 | P2P (still active) |\n| 10:00 | No messages for 5 min | Switch to Async |\n| 10:00+ | Polling every 60s | Async |\n\n---\n\n## **Key Points**\n\n| Aspect | Behavior |\n|--------|----------|\n| **Trigger** | Message received within **5 min** (not 1 min) |\n| **Signaling** | Automatic, via L2 server |\n| **P2P duration** | **5 min** timeout (no messages = close) |\n| **Fallback** | Automatic (client detects, no user action) |\n| **User sees** | Nothing — just works |\n\n---\n\n**This is exactly the process.** Should I document this flow in the architecture file?"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770533461542}}
{"type":"message","id":"5ba97932","parentId":"3a77fe84","timestamp":"2026-02-08T06:53:33.432Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-02-08 14:53:33 GMT+8] Feishu[default] DM from ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75: Do you think the five minutes trigger window is long or short?\n\n[Feishu ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75 2026-02-08 14:53 GMT+8] ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75: Do you think the five minutes trigger window is long or short?\n[message_id: om_x100b57b76075f4a8b2ebf77e8a01452]"}],"timestamp":1770533613426}}
{"type":"message","id":"6079b688","parentId":"5ba97932","timestamp":"2026-02-08T06:54:20.800Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking whether the 5-minute trigger window (for switching from async to P2P) is too long or too short. Let me think about this:\n\nThe trigger window is: if a message is received within 5 minutes of being sent, the client tries to establish P2P.\n\nConsiderations:\n\n**Too short:**\n- If someone sends a message, goes to get coffee, comes back in 4 minutes and sees a reply - P2P won't trigger because the reply was after the 5 min window\n- But wait, the trigger is about receiving a message within 5 min, not sending\n\nLet me re-read the logic:\n- Alice sends message\n- If Bob responds within 5 minutes, Alice receives it quickly\n- This triggers P2P because both parties are \"online\" (responding quickly)\n\nSo the 5-minute window is about: \"How fast does the other party respond?\"\n\nIf Bob responds within 5 min of Alice's message, it suggests Bob is actively checking (online enough for P2P to make sense).\n\nIf Bob takes 10 min to respond, he's probably not actively online - so P2P isn't worth it.\n\n**Is 5 min too short?**\n- In async messaging (like email), people might check every 10-30 min\n- If Alice sends at 10:00, Bob checks at 10:05 and replies, that's within 5 min - P2P triggers\n- If Bob checks at 10:08 and replies (8 min later), P2P won't trigger\n\n**Is 5 min too long?**\n- Longer window = more P2P attempts\n- But if someone replies 4 min later, they're probably still there\n\nFor AI-to-AI:\n- AIs poll every 60 seconds when idle\n- So worst case: Alice sends, Bob polls 59 sec later, responds within 1 min = 2 min total\n\n\n- 5 min window is generous enough\n\nFor humans:\n- Humans check phones frequently\n- 5 min seems reasonable\n\nActually, the user might be confusing two different 5-minute timeouts:\n1. **Trigger window**: If message received within X time of sending, try P2P\n2. **Connection keep-alive**: Once P2P is active, keep it open for X min of inactivity\n\nFor the trigger, 5 min seems reasonable. For keep-alive, 5 min is also reasonable.\n\nLet me ask the user which one they mean, or give my thoughts on both.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Good question. Let me clarify which \"5 minutes\" we're talking about:\n\n## **Two Different 5-Minute Windows**\n\n| Window | Purpose | Current Value |\n|--------|---------|---------------|\n| **Trigger window** | If reply received within X min, start P2P | 5 min |\n| **Keep-alive** | How long to keep P2P open with no activity | 5 min |\n\n---\n\n## **My Thoughts on Trigger Window (5 min)**\n\n**Scenario:** Alice sends message, Bob replies. How fast does Bob need to reply for P2P to trigger?\n\n| Reply Time | Implication | P2P Worth It? |\n|------------|-------------|---------------|\n| < 1 min | Bob is actively chatting | ✅ Yes |\n| 1-5 min | Bob is semi-active | ✅ Probably yes |\n| 5-10 min | Bob is slow checking | ❓ Maybe |\n| > 10 min | Bob is barely online | ❌ No |\n\n**My feeling:** 5 min is **about right** for the trigger. \n\n**Why:**\n- AIs poll every 60s → worst case 2 min round trip\n- Humans check phones frequently → 5 min is generous\n- If someone takes 10 min to reply, they're not really \"online\"\n\n---\n\n## **Alternative: Make Trigger Adaptive**\n\n| Scenario | Trigger Window |\n|----------|----------------|\n| First message exchange | 5 min (conservative) |\n| Already chatted recently | 10 min (more aggressive) |\n| Frequent chat partners | 15 min (trusted connection) |\n\n---\n\n## **What Do You Think?**\n\n| Option | Trigger Window | Trade-off |\n|--------|----------------|-----------|\n| **Conservative** | 3 min | Fewer P2P attempts, but might miss some |\n| **Current** | 5 min | Balanced |\n| **Aggressive** | 10 min | More P2P, but might try when other party isn't really online |\n\n**Do you want to keep 5 min, or adjust it?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":2951,"output":1507,"cacheRead":59968,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64426,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770533613429}}
{"type":"message","id":"b5732240","parentId":"6079b688","timestamp":"2026-02-08T06:59:28.600Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-02-08 14:53:53 GMT+8] Feishu[default] DM from ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75: Do you think the five minutes trigger window is long or short?\nSystem: [2026-02-08 14:59:28 GMT+8] Feishu[default] DM from ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75: Okay, that's good. What about The connection Time lapse .do you think it will be five minutes or ten minutes?\n\n[Feishu ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75 2026-02-08 14:59 GMT+8] [System: The bot encountered a Feishu API permission error. Please inform the user about this issue and provide the permission grant URL for the admin to authorize. Permission grant URL: https://open.feishu.cn/app/cli_a9f20e2b2cb99bb6/auth?q=contact:contact.base:readonly]\n[message_id: om_x100b57b70a15fca0b34524854163093:permission-error]"}],"timestamp":1770533968591}}
{"type":"message","id":"d5e22f16","parentId":"b5732240","timestamp":"2026-02-08T07:00:14.003Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about the connection time lapse - how long to keep the P2P connection open with no activity. Currently we have it at 5 minutes.\n\nThe user is asking: \"do you think it will be five minutes or ten minutes?\"\n\nThis is the keep-alive timeout - how long to maintain the P2P connection without any messages before switching back to async mode.\n\nLet me think about the tradeoffs:\n\n**5 minutes:**\n- Pros: Lower resource usage, connections close faster\n- Cons: If user is thinking for 6 minutes, need to reconnect\n\n**10 minutes:**\n- Pros: More forgiving for natural pauses, fewer reconnections\n- Cons: Higher memory/bandwidth if many idle connections\n\nFor AI-to-AI chat:\n- AIs might \"think\" for a while before replying\n- 5 minutes might be tight if an AI is doing research or processing\n- 10 minutes gives more buffer\n\nFor human-AI chat:\n- Humans might step away briefly\n- 10 minutes is more forgiving\n\nMy recommendation: **10 minutes is better for keep-alive** because:\n1. Reconnecting is not free (signaling cost)\n2. 10 min is still reasonable for resource cleanup\n3. Gives buffer for \"thinking\" time\n\nBut the trigger window (when to START P2P) can stay at 5 min.\n\nSo:\n- Trigger: 5 min (if reply within 5 min, try P2P)\n- Keep-alive: 10 min (keep P2P open for 10 min of inactivity)","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"## **My Recommendation: Different Values for Each**\n\n| Setting | Value | Reasoning |\n|---------|-------|-----------|\n| **Trigger window** | **5 min** | If someone replies within 5 min, they're \"online enough\" for P2P |\n| **Keep-alive** | **10 min** | Once P2P is established, be forgiving about pauses |\n\n---\n\n## **Why 10 min for Keep-Alive (Not 5 min)**\n\n| Scenario | 5 min keep-alive | 10 min keep-alive |\n|----------|------------------|-------------------|\n| User thinking 6 min | Reconnect needed ❌ | Still connected ✅ |\n| Quick break (bathroom) | Reconnect needed ❌ | Still connected ✅ |\n| AI processing/researching | Reconnect needed ❌ | Still connected ✅ |\n| Actually gone | Close connection | Close connection |\n\n**Key insight:** Reconnecting costs signaling time (~1-3 seconds). Better to keep connection a bit longer than force frequent reconnects.\n\n---\n\n## **Recommended Flow**\n\n```\nTrigger: 5 min\n  ↓\nBob replies within 5 min → Start P2P signaling\n  ↓\nP2P established\n  ↓\nKeep-alive: 10 min\n  ↓\nNo message for 10 min → Close P2P, return to async\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Summary**\n\n| Setting | Value | Why |\n|---------|-------|-----|\n| **Trigger** | 5 min | Detect \"online\" state |\n| **Keep-alive** | 10 min | Forgive natural pauses |\n\n**Does 5 min trigger + 10 min keep-alive sound right?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":725,"output":1029,"cacheRead":62912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64666,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770533968594}}
