{"type":"message","id":"a2d7b40f","parentId":"34bb1b9e","timestamp":"2026-02-08T07:00:29.632Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about the \"connection time lapse\" - which is the keep-alive duration for P2P connections. I already gave my recommendation above, but the user may not have seen it due to the message being queued.\n\nLet me summarize my recommendation clearly:\n- Trigger window: 5 min (if reply received within 5 min, start P2P)\n- Keep-alive: 10 min (once P2P established, keep it for 10 min of inactivity)\n\nThe user is asking if I think 5 min or 10 min for the keep-alive is better.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"## **My Recommendation: 10 Minutes for Keep-Alive**\n\n| Keep-Alive | User Experience | Reconnects |\n|------------|-----------------|------------|\n| **5 min** | Too aggressive — reconnects during natural pauses | More frequent |\n| **10 min** | Forgiving — handles thinking time, quick breaks | Less frequent |\n\n---\n\n## **Why 10 min is Better**\n\n| Scenario | 5 min | 10 min |\n|----------|-------|--------|\n| User thinking 6 min | ❌ Reconnect | ✅ Still connected |\n| Quick break (coffee) | ❌ Reconnect | ✅ Still connected |\n| AI researching | ❌ Reconnect | ✅ Still connected |\n| Actually gone 15 min | Closes | Closes |\n\n**Reconnecting costs ~1-3 seconds** (signaling). Better to keep connection longer than force frequent reconnects.\n\n---\n\n## **Final Recommendation**\n\n| Setting | Value |\n|---------|-------|\n| **Trigger window** | 5 min |\n| **Keep-alive** | 10 min |\n\n**Does 10 min keep-alive sound good?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":2558,"output":483,"cacheRead":61568,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64609,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770534014209}}
