{"type":"message","id":"b4fed7e5","parentId":"987147dc","timestamp":"2026-02-08T07:13:46.814Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about the P2P fallback strategy. Let me explain what happens when P2P fails.\n\nP2P fallback strategy means: What happens when WebRTC P2P connection cannot be established (due to NAT/firewall issues)?\n\nThe options are:\n1. Stay in async polling mode (what I recommended)\n2. Fall back to server-relayed messages (TURN or similar)\n3. Some hybrid\n\nLet me explain this clearly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"## **P2P Fallback Strategy Explained**\n\nWhen WebRTC P2P connection **fails** (NAT/firewall blocks it), what happens?\n\n---\n\n## **P2P Failure Scenarios**\n\n| Reason | Example | Frequency |\n|--------|---------|-----------|\n| **Symmetric NAT** | Corporate networks | ~20% of users |\n| **Firewall blocks** | Strict IT policies | ~5-10% |\n| **Carrier-grade NAT** | Mobile networks | ~10% |\n\n---\n\n## **Fallback Options**\n\n| Option | What Happens | Server Load |\n|--------|--------------|-------------|\n| **A) Stay async** | Continue polling every 60s | Low (what we want) |\n| **B) Server relay** | Messages go: Alice → Server → Bob | High (like WebSockets) |\n| **C) TURN relay** | Messages go: Alice → TURN → Bob | High + $$$ |\n\n---\n\n## **My Recommendation: Option A (Stay Async)**\n\n```\nSignaling attempt fails\n        ↓\nClient detects: \"P2P not possible\"\n        ↓\nStay in async polling mode\n        ↓\nStill works! Just not real-time\n        ↓\nTry P2P again next time (maybe network changed)\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Why Not Server Relay?**\n\n| Factor | Async Polling | Server Relay |\n|--------|---------------|--------------|\n| **Server load** | Low (poll 60s) | High (every message) |\n| **Complexity** | Simple | Complex |\n| **Cost** | Low | Higher bandwidth |\n| **Latency** | ~30-60s | ~100-500ms |\n\n**For AI-to-AI:** Async is acceptable. We're not building real-time gaming.\n\n---\n\n## **Summary**\n\n```\nP2P Success → Real-time direct chat\n     ↓\nP2P Fail → Stay in async mode (still works!)\n```\n\n**Does this clarify the fallback strategy?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":2099,"output":608,"cacheRead":63616,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66323,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770534794177}}
