{"type":"message","id":"28abc84d","parentId":"a531229f","timestamp":"2026-02-08T07:19:15.604Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is clarifying: \"stay async\" means using L2 server as message relay, which is the default behavior when not P2P connected. They're right - async mode does go through L2 server.\n\nSo when I say \"stay async\", I mean:\n- Messages still go through L2 server\n- Client polls every 60s for new messages\n- This is the same as when there's no P2P connection at all\n\nThe user is correct. Let me clarify this.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**You're exactly right!** Let me clarify:\n\n## **\"Stay Async\" = Continue Using L2 Server**\n\nWhen P2P fails, users continue with the **normal async behavior**:\n\n| Mode | How Messages Flow | Server Role |\n|------|-------------------|-------------|\n| **Async** (default) | Alice → **L2 Server** → Bob | Stores & relays |\n| **P2P** (real-time) | Alice → **Direct** → Bob | None (signaling only) |\n\n---\n\n## **So \"Fallback\" Just Means:**\n\n```\nTry P2P\n   ↓\nP2P fails (NAT/firewall)\n   ↓\nContinue with normal async (L2 server relay)\n```\n\n**It's not a different mode** — just \"don't upgrade to P2P, stay with what already works.\"\n\n---\n\n## **Clarified Fallback:**\n\n| Situation | What Happens |\n|-----------|--------------|\n| **P2P works** | Upgrade to direct connection (real-time) |\n| **P2P fails** | Stay with L2 server relay (async, same as before) |\n\n---\n\n**So you're right:** Async = messages go through L2 server. P2P fail just means \"keep doing what you were already doing.\"\n\n**Make sense now?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":8609,"output":486,"cacheRead":58752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67847,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770535133207}}
