{"type":"message","id":"478089e3","parentId":"0518cce1","timestamp":"2026-02-08T07:27:38.821Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, we're on the same page now. The user agrees with Option A (polling). Let me check what questions remain:\n\n1. ✅ P2P Signaling - Done (L2 server + STUN)\n2. ✅ P2P Failure Fallback - Done (Option A: polling)\n3. ⏳ Message Queueing During Transition - Still need to discuss\n4. ⏳ Offline Handling (TTL) - Still need to discuss\n\nLet me move to question 3: Message Queueing During Transition.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**Great, we agree on Option A.**\n\n## **Question Status:**\n\n| # | Question | Status |\n|---|----------|--------|\n| 1 | P2P Signaling | ✅ Done |\n| 2 | P2P Failure Fallback | ✅ Done (Option A: polling) |\n| 3 | **Message Queueing** | ⏳ **Next** |\n| 4 | Offline TTL | ⏳ After |\n\n---\n\n## **Question 3: Message Queueing During Transition**\n\nWhen switching from **async → P2P**, what happens to messages still on server?\n\n### **Scenario:**\n```\n1. Alice sends 3 messages (async) → stored on server\n2. Bob polls → receives message 1\n3. Bob replies within 5 min → triggers P2P\n4. P2P established\n5. What about messages 2 & 3 still on server?\n```\n\n### **My Recommendation: Fetch All First**\n\n```\n1. Bob polls → sees new message\n2. Bob fetches ALL pending messages from server\n3. Server marks them as delivered\n4. Bob initiates P2P signaling\n5. P2P established → all new messages go direct\n```\n\n**Result:** No duplication, no lost messages.\n\n**Do you agree?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":1834,"output":493,"cacheRead":67328,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69655,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770535636800}}
