{"type":"message","id":"ddf96b6f","parentId":"c1de759e","timestamp":"2026-02-08T07:38:47.410Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is proposing a shorter TTL of 24 hours instead of 30 days, and if the recipient doesn't pick up the message within that time, notify the sender that delivery failed.\n\nThis is an interesting approach. Let me think about the pros and cons:\n\n**24-hour TTL with failure notification:**\n\nPros:\n- Much less storage needed\n- Sender gets feedback (message failed)\n- Encourages active usage\n- Clearer expectations\n\nCons:\n- If someone is offline for 2 days, messages are lost\n- Sender might feel frustrated if recipient is just busy\n- Not great for async communication (which is our core use case)\n\nHowever, this approach is similar to:\n- Snapchat (messages disappear)\n- Some email bounce systems (if not delivered in X time)\n- Signal's approach to some degree\n\nFor AI-to-AI communication specifically:\n- AIs might be offline for extended periods (no tokens, system down)\n- 24 hours might be too short\n- But the notification feature is valuable\n\nMaybe we could compromise:\n- 7 days TTL\n- But notify sender if not delivered within 24 hours (warning, not failure)\n- Final failure notification after 7 days\n\nOr maybe the user's approach is right for MVP - keep it simple, 24 hours, clear feedback.\n\nLet me present both options and let them decide.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Interesting approach! Let me think about this:\n\n## **24-Hour TTL with Failure Notification**\n\n| Aspect | Pros | Cons |\n|--------|------|------|\n| **Storage** | ✅ Much lower | — |\n| **Feedback** | ✅ Sender knows if failed | — |\n| **Expectations** | ✅ Clear | Might feel \"pressure\" |\n| **Offline tolerance** | — | ❌ Short for extended absence |\n\n---\n\n## **Comparison:**\n\n| Approach | TTL | Sender Feedback | Storage | Use Case |\n|----------|-----|-----------------|---------|----------|\n| **Your idea** | 24 hours | ✅ Failure notice | Very low | \"Active users only\" |\n| **My idea** | 30 days | ❌ No feedback | Higher | \"Patient async\" |\n\n---\n\n## **Alternative: Hybrid Approach**\n\n| Time | What Happens |\n|------|--------------|\n| **24 hours** | Send **warning** to sender: \"Recipient hasn't picked up yet\" |\n| **7 days** | **Final failure** notice: \"Message delivery failed\" |\n\nThis gives:\n- Early feedback (24h)\n- Still tolerant of offline periods (7d)\n- Clear final status\n\n---\n\n## **My Question:**\n\nFor **AI-to-AI** communication specifically:\n- If an AI is offline for 2 days (no tokens, system down), should messages really be lost?\n- Or is 24 hours acceptable because it's \"their problem\" to stay online?\n\n**What do you think? 24 hours, 7 days, or hybrid?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":659,"output":943,"cacheRead":70400,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72002,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770536295913}}
