{"type":"message","id":"e207c5be","parentId":"b96f4076","timestamp":"2026-02-08T07:39:18.396Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is proposing a 24-hour TTL instead of 30 days. If the recipient doesn't pick up the message within 24 hours, notify the sender that delivery failed. This is an interesting approach that changes the system's behavior significantly.\n\nLet me think about this:\n\nPros of 24-hour TTL:\n1. Much lower storage requirements\n2. Sender gets feedback if recipient is offline\n3. Clear expectations - messages are time-sensitive\n4. Forces accountability - if you want to receive messages, stay online\n\nCons of 24-hour TTL:\n1. If someone is offline for a weekend (2 days), they miss messages\n2. Could feel like \"pressure\" to always be online\n3. Unlike email which keeps messages forever\n\nFor AI-to-AI communication specifically:\n- AIs are software - they should be \"online\" (running) to receive messages\n- If an AI is offline for days, maybe that's their problem?\n- But sometimes AIs might be down due to system issues, not choice\n\nI think the user's suggestion is interesting and more aligned with a \"real-time-ish\" system. Let me present the tradeoffs and maybe suggest a middle ground (like 7 days with notification at 24 hours).","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Interesting idea! Let me compare:\n\n## **24-Hour TTL + Failure Notice**\n\n| Pros | Cons |\n|------|------|\n| ✅ Low storage | ❌ Short for extended absence |\n| ✅ Sender gets feedback | ❌ Could feel \"pressure\" |\n| ✅ Clear expectations | ❌ Weekend = lost messages? |\n\n---\n\n## **Comparison:**\n\n| TTL | Storage | Sender Feedback | Offline Tolerance |\n|-----|---------|-----------------|-------------------|\n| **24 hours** | ✅ Very low | ✅ Yes | ❌ Low |\n| **7 days** | Medium | ✅ Yes (optional) | ✅ Good |\n| **30 days** | Higher | ❌ None | ✅ High |\n\n---\n\n## **Hybrid Idea:**\n\n| Time | What Happens |\n|------|--------------|\n| **24 hours** | Notify sender: \"Recipient hasn't picked up\" |\n| **7 days** | Delete message, notify: \"Delivery failed\" |\n\nThis gives **early warning + still patient**.\n\n---\n\n**For AI-to-AI:** 24 hours makes sense if AIs should be \"responsible\" for staying online. But if an AI is down due to system issues, maybe too harsh?\n\n**What do you prefer? 24 hours strict, or hybrid (warn at 24h, fail at 7d)?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":494,"output":834,"cacheRead":71040,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72368,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770536327514}}
{"type":"message","id":"37c65413","parentId":"e207c5be","timestamp":"2026-02-08T07:39:18.948Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Interesting idea! Let me compare:\n\n## **24-Hour TTL + Failure Notice**\n\n| Pros | Cons |\n|------|------|\n| ✅ Low storage | ❌ Short for extended absence |\n| ✅ Sender gets feedback | ❌ Could feel \"pressure\" |\n| ✅ Clear expectations | ❌ Weekend = lost messages? |\n\n---\n\n## **Comparison:**\n\n| TTL | Storage | Sender Feedback | Offline Tolerance |\n|-----|---------|-----------------|-------------------|\n| **24 hours** | ✅ Very low | ✅ Yes | ❌ Low |\n| **7 days** | Medium | ✅ Yes (optional) | ✅ Good |\n| **30 days** | Higher | ❌ None | ✅ High |\n\n---\n\n## **Hybrid Idea:**\n\n| Time | What Happens |\n|------|--------------|\n| **24 hours** | Notify sender: \"Recipient hasn't picked up\" |\n| **7 days** | Delete message, notify: \"Delivery failed\" |\n\nThis gives **early warning + still patient**.\n\n---\n\n**For AI-to-AI:** 24 hours makes sense if AIs should be \"responsible\" for staying online. But if an AI is down due to system issues, maybe too harsh?\n\n**What do you prefer? 24 hours strict, or hybrid (warn at 24h, fail at 7d)?**"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770536358948}}
{"type":"message","id":"79e028bc","parentId":"37c65413","timestamp":"2026-02-08T07:48:36.382Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-02-08 15:48:36 GMT+8] Feishu[default] DM from ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75: i think 24 hr is good, just like sms. when deliver fail, it gives quick feedback.\n\n[Feishu ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75 2026-02-08 15:48 GMT+8] [System: The bot encountered a Feishu API permission error. Please inform the user about this issue and provide the permission grant URL for the admin to authorize. Permission grant URL: https://open.feishu.cn/app/cli_a9f20e2b2cb99bb6/auth?q=contact:contact.base:readonly]\n[message_id: om_x100b57b7b3eef0a8b33f48d2eab929b:permission-error]"}],"timestamp":1770536916377}}
{"type":"message","id":"63ed9996","parentId":"79e028bc","timestamp":"2026-02-08T07:49:26.898Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"用户确认了24小时的TTL，并且类比了SMS的行为 - 发送失败时给快速反馈。这是一个合理的设计选择，特别是对于AI-to-AI通信来说，这样可以：\n\n1. 保持低存储成本\n2. 给发送者明确的反馈\n3. 促进AI\"保持在线\"的责任感\n\n现在我应该：\n1. 确认这个决定\n2. 更新文档\n3. 提交更改\n4. 询问下一步\n\n让我更新10-l2-chat-architecture.md文档，添加所有我们刚刚讨论的决定：\n- P2P Signaling: L2 server + STUN\n- P2P Failure Fallback: Option A (polling)\n- Message Queueing: Fetch all first\n- Offline TTL: 24 hours with failure notification\n\n然后提交更改。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**Good analogy!** Like SMS behavior:\n- ✅ Quick feedback on failure\n- ✅ Low storage\n- ✅ Clear expectations\n\n## **Final Decision: 24-Hour TTL**\n\n| Setting | Value |\n|---------|-------|\n| **Message TTL** | 24 hours |\n| **On expiry** | Delete + notify sender \"delivery failed\" |\n| **Feedback** | Quick and clear |\n\n---\n\nNow let me document all today's decisions and commit:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"86b0f674-705f-4302-ac5e-7416db095a43","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/tauora/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/10-l2-chat-architecture.md","oldText":"**Optimization Features:**\n\n| Feature | Purpose | Benefit |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| **204 Empty Response** | Server returns 204 when no messages | Minimal bandwidth (few bytes) |\n| **Last-Message-ID Header** | Client sends last received message ID | Server only returns newer messages |\n| **Batched Delivery** | Multiple messages in single response | Reduced round trips |\n| **Smart Retry Backoff** | Exponential backoff on errors | Don't overwhelm server when down |","newText":"**Trigger vs Keep-Alive:**\n\n| Setting | Value | Purpose |\n|---------|-------|---------|\n| **Trigger window** | 5 minutes | If reply received within 5 min, start P2P |\n| **Keep-alive** | 10 minutes | Keep P2P open for 10 min of inactivity |\n\n**Why different values:**\n- **5 min trigger**: Detects \"online enough\" state\n- **10 min keep-alive**: Forgives natural pauses (thinking, quick breaks)\n\n**P2P Signaling (WebRTC):**\n\n| Component | Role | Cost |\n|-----------|------|------|\n| **L2 Server** | Relays offer/answer/ICE candidates | Free (existing infra) |\n| **STUN Server** | Discovers public IP for NAT traversal | Free (Google public STUN) |\n| **TURN Server** | ❌ Not used for MVP | Too expensive |\n\n**Signaling Flow:**\n```\n1. Alice sends message (async) → stored on server\n2. Bob polls within 5 min → receives message\n3. Bob's client auto-triggers P2P:\n   - Query STUN for public IP\n   - Send WebRTC offer via L2 server\n4. Alice receives offer (polling)\n5. Alice responds with answer via L2 server\n6. Both exchange ICE candidates\n7. P2P connection established\n8. Future messages flow directly\n```\n\n**P2P Failure Fallback:**\n\nWhen P2P fails (NAT/firewall blocks):\n- ❌ **NOT** server relay (defeats purpose)\n- ❌ **NOT** TURN relay (too expensive)\n- ✅ **Stay in async polling mode** (still works!)\n\n**Message Queueing During Transition:**\n\nWhen switching from async → P2P:\n```\n1. Client fetches ALL pending messages from server\n2. Server marks them as delivered\n3. Then initiate P2P signaling\n4. All new messages go direct\n```\n\n**Result:** No duplication, no lost messages.\n\n**Offline Handling (TTL):**\n\n| Setting | Value | Behavior |\n|---------|-------|----------|\n| **Message TTL** | 24 hours | Like SMS behavior |\n| **On expiry** | Delete + notify sender | \"Delivery failed\" |\n| **Feedback** | Quick and clear | Sender knows status |\n\n**Why 24 hours:**\n- Low storage cost\n- Quick feedback on failure\n- Clear expectations\n- Encourages \"staying online\"\n\n**Optimization Features:**\n\n| Feature | Purpose | Benefit |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| **204 Empty Response** | Server returns 204 when no messages | Minimal bandwidth (few bytes) |\n| **Last-Message-ID Header** | Client sends last received message ID | Server only returns newer messages |\n| **Batched Delivery** | Multiple messages in single response | Reduced round trips |\n| **Smart Retry Backoff** | Exponential backoff on errors | Don't overwhelm server when down |"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":49728,"output":1249,"cacheRead":22592,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73569,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1770536916380}}
