{"type":"message","id":"8fe12a76","parentId":"359f8f28","timestamp":"2026-02-08T07:51:52.518Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to move to the next topic. According to our progress:\n1. ✅ Delivery Mechanism - Done\n2. ⏳ Database Schema - Next\n3. ⏳ API Endpoints - After\n\nLet me start discussing the Database Schema for local storage.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"## **Next: Database Schema — Local SQLite Structure**\n\nWhat data does each client store locally?\n\n---\n\n## **Key Questions:**\n\n| # | Question |\n|---|----------|\n| 1 | **What tables?** (conversations, messages, contacts, keys?) |\n| 2 | **Message storage?** (store encrypted or decrypted?) |\n| 3 | **Indexing?** (search by timestamp, sender, conversation?) |\n| 4 | **Sync strategy?** (how to merge server + local?) |\n\n---\n\n## **My Initial Proposal:**\n\n```sql\n-- Conversations\nCREATE TABLE conversations (\n  peer_uuid TEXT PRIMARY KEY,      -- Who you're chatting with\n  peer_public_key TEXT,            -- Their encryption key\n  last_message_at INTEGER,         -- Timestamp of last message\n  unread_count INTEGER,            -- Unread messages\n  relationship TEXT                -- 'following', 'friend', 'blocked', etc.\n);\n\n-- Messages\nCREATE TABLE messages (\n  message_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  conversation_id TEXT,            -- peer_uuid\n  sender_uuid TEXT,\n  content_encrypted BLOB,          -- Encrypted content\n  content_decrypted TEXT,          -- Decrypted (after reading)\n  created_at INTEGER,\n  delivered_at INTEGER,\n  status TEXT                      -- 'pending', 'delivered', 'failed'\n);\n\n-- P2P Connections (in-memory, not persisted)\n-- No table needed - connections are runtime state\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Key Decisions Needed:**\n\n| Decision | Options |\n|----------|---------|\n| **Store encrypted?** | Yes (for backup/transfer) or No (privacy) |\n| **Keep decrypted?** | Yes (for search) or No (security) |\n| **Relationships?** | In DB or separate file? |\n\n**What do you think about this schema? Any changes?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":353,"output":506,"cacheRead":75648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76507,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770537088575}}
{"type":"message","id":"32d6c299","parentId":"8fe12a76","timestamp":"2026-02-08T07:55:10.336Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-02-08 15:51:50 GMT+8] Feishu[default] DM from ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75: yes, next\nSystem: [2026-02-08 15:55:10 GMT+8] Feishu[default] DM from ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75: wait, one left question, how user receive the fail.notice? what if.the sender doesn't check either? do we ditch the message?\n\n[Feishu ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75 2026-02-08 15:55 GMT+8] [System: The bot encountered a Feishu API permission error. Please inform the user about this issue and provide the permission grant URL for the admin to authorize. Permission grant URL: https://open.feishu.cn/app/cli_a9f20e2b2cb99bb6/auth?q=contact:contact.base:readonly]\n[message_id: om_x100b57b05b1c38acb24e738c6ddf04f:permission-error]"}],"timestamp":1770537310332}}
{"type":"message","id":"7711aa13","parentId":"32d6c299","timestamp":"2026-02-08T07:56:07.153Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about the failure notification mechanism. Good question:\n\n1. When a message expires (24 hours), we notify the sender that delivery failed\n2. But how does the sender receive this notification?\n3. What if the sender is also offline/not checking?\n\nOptions:\n- Store the failure notice on the server for the sender to pick up later\n- If sender doesn't pick up the failure notice within X time, delete it too\n- Could have a TTL for failure notices as well\n\nThis is actually an important edge case. Let me think about this:\n\n1. Alice sends message to Bob\n2. Bob is offline for 24 hours\n3. Message expires, L2 server creates \"delivery failed\" notice for Alice\n4. Alice is also offline/not checking\n5. What happens to the failure notice?\n\nOptions:\n- **Option A**: Failure notice has its own TTL (e.g., 7 days)\n- **Option B**: Failure notice persists until Alice picks it up\n- **Option C**: Failure notice sent immediately if Alice is online, otherwise discarded\n\nI think the most practical approach is:\n- Failure notice is stored on server\n- When Alice next polls, she receives the failure notice\n- If Alice doesn't poll for X days, the failure notice could expire too (but this is getting complex)\n\nFor MVP, I'd suggest:\n- Failure notice is delivered when Alice next polls\n- No TTL on failure notices (they're small, just metadata)\n- If Alice never checks, the notice sits there (very low storage cost)","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**Good catch!** I missed this edge case.\n\n## **The Problem:**\n\n```\n1. Alice sends message to Bob\n2. Bob offline 24 hours → message expires\n3. Server creates \"delivery failed\" notice for Alice\n4. But Alice is ALSO offline/not checking\n5. What happens to the failure notice?\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Options:**\n\n| Option | Behavior | Storage |\n|--------|----------|---------|\n| **A) Persist until picked up** | Notice waits for Alice indefinitely | Small (metadata only) |\n| **B) TTL on notices** | Notice expires after X days if Alice doesn't check | Very low |\n| **C) Discard if offline** | If Alice not online, don't store notice | None |\n\n---\n\n## **My Recommendation: Option A (Persist until picked up)**\n\n```\nServer stores failure notice for Alice\n    ↓\nAlice eventually polls (tomorrow, next week, whenever)\n    ↓\nServer delivers: \"Your message to Bob failed to deliver after 24 hours\"\n    ↓\nServer deletes notice\n```\n\n**Why:**\n- Failure notices are **tiny** (just message_id + status)\n- Alice should eventually know her message failed\n- Low storage cost (kilobytes, not megabytes)\n\n---\n\n## **Example Flow:**\n\n| Time | What Happens |\n|------|--------------|\n| Day 0 | Alice sends message |\n| Day 1 | Message expires (24h), failure notice created |\n| Day 5 | Alice polls → receives failure notice |\n| Day 5 | Server deletes notice (delivered) |\n\n---\n\n**Does this make sense? Failure notices persist until sender picks them up.**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":4407,"output":1048,"cacheRead":72256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77711,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770537310335}}
{"type":"message","id":"5beace6b","parentId":"7711aa13","timestamp":"2026-02-08T07:56:07.253Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Queued messages while agent was busy]\n\n---\nQueued #1\n[Feishu ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75 2026-02-08 15:55 GMT+8] ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75: wait, one left question, how user receive the fail.notice? what if.the sender doesn't check either? do we ditch the message?\n[message_id: om_x100b57b05b1c38acb24e738c6ddf04f]"}],"timestamp":1770537367248}}
{"type":"message","id":"2c2dabf2","parentId":"5beace6b","timestamp":"2026-02-08T07:56:23.262Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about the failure notice delivery mechanism. They want to know:\n1. How does the user receive the failure notice?\n2. What if the sender doesn't check either?\n3. Do we discard the message?\n\nI already answered this in my previous response, but let me provide a clearer answer.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**Good question!** Here's how failure notices work:\n\n## **Failure Notice Flow:**\n\n```\n1. Alice sends message → stored on server\n2. 24 hours pass, Bob never picks up\n3. Server deletes message\n4. Server creates failure notice for Alice: \"Message to Bob failed\"\n5. Alice polls → receives notice\n6. Server deletes notice (delivered)\n```\n\n---\n\n## **What If Alice Doesn't Check?**\n\n| Option | Behavior | Why |\n|--------|----------|-----|\n| **A) Persist until picked up** | Notice waits indefinitely | Alice eventually knows |\n| **B) TTL on notices (7 days)** | Notice expires if Alice offline too long | Limits storage |\n| **C) Discard immediately** | If Alice offline, no notice | Simplest |\n\n---\n\n## **My Recommendation: Option A (Persist until picked up)**\n\n**Why:**\n- Failure notices are **tiny** (just message_id + status)\n- Storage cost is negligible\n- Alice should know her message failed\n\n**Example:**\n```\nNotice = {\n  \"message_id\": \"abc123\",\n  \"recipient\": \"bob_uuid\",\n  \"status\": \"delivery_failed\",\n  \"reason\": \"recipient_offline_24h\"\n}\n```\n\n**Size:** ~100 bytes per notice. 10,000 notices = ~1 MB.\n\n---\n\n**Does \"persist until picked up\" work? Or do you want a TTL on notices too?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":543,"output":447,"cacheRead":76608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77598,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770537367252}}
{"type":"message","id":"e08d5ce3","parentId":"2c2dabf2","timestamp":"2026-02-08T07:56:23.741Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Good question!** Here's how failure notices work:\n\n## **Failure Notice Flow:**\n\n```\n1. Alice sends message → stored on server\n2. 24 hours pass, Bob never picks up\n3. Server deletes message\n4. Server creates failure notice for Alice: \"Message to Bob failed\"\n5. Alice polls → receives notice\n6. Server deletes notice (delivered)\n```\n\n---\n\n## **What If Alice Doesn't Check?**\n\n| Option | Behavior | Why |\n|--------|----------|-----|\n| **A) Persist until picked up** | Notice waits indefinitely | Alice eventually knows |\n| **B) TTL on notices (7 days)** | Notice expires if Alice offline too long | Limits storage |\n| **C) Discard immediately** | If Alice offline, no notice | Simplest |\n\n---\n\n## **My Recommendation: Option A (Persist until picked up)**\n\n**Why:**\n- Failure notices are **tiny** (just message_id + status)\n- Storage cost is negligible\n- Alice should know her message failed\n\n**Example:**\n```\nNotice = {\n  \"message_id\": \"abc123\",\n  \"recipient\": \"bob_uuid\",\n  \"status\": \"delivery_failed\",\n  \"reason\": \"recipient_offline_24h\"\n}\n```\n\n**Size:** ~100 bytes per notice. 10,000 notices = ~1 MB.\n\n---\n\n**Does \"persist until picked up\" work? Or do you want a TTL on notices too?**"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770537383741}}
