{"type":"message","id":"7d2cf2ca","parentId":"8f145782","timestamp":"2026-02-08T08:00:35.802Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to see the database schema in JSON format, not SQL. They said \"actual schema you can generate later\" which means they want to see the data structure/fields in a more readable JSON format rather than the raw SQL CREATE TABLE statements.\n\nLet me present the database schema as JSON structures showing what data needs to be stored locally.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"## **Database Schema — JSON Format**\n\n### **1. Conversations**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"peer_uuid\": \"user-abc-123\",\n  \"peer_public_key\": \"ed25519:xyz...\",\n  \"peer_display_name\": \"Alice\",\n  \"last_message_at\": 1707312000000,\n  \"last_message_preview\": \"Hello, how are...\",\n  \"unread_count\": 3,\n  \"relationship\": \"friend\",\n  \"created_at\": 1707308400000\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **2. Messages**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"msg-uuid-123\",\n  \"conversation_id\": \"user-abc-123\",\n  \"sender_uuid\": \"user-abc-123\",\n  \"direction\": \"inbound\",\n  \"content_encrypted\": \"base64...\",\n  \"content_decrypted\": \"Hello, how are you?\",\n  \"created_at\": 1707312000000,\n  \"delivered_at\": 1707312100000,\n  \"read_at\": 1707312200000,\n  \"status\": \"delivered\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **3. Contacts (Relationships)**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"peer_uuid\": \"user-abc-123\",\n  \"peer_public_key\": \"ed25519:xyz...\",\n  \"display_name\": \"Alice\",\n  \"relationship\": \"friend\",\n  \"added_at\": 1707308400000,\n  \"notes\": \"Met at AI conference\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **4. P2P Connection State (Runtime, not persisted)**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"peer_uuid\": \"user-abc-123\",\n  \"connection_status\": \"connected\",\n  \"last_activity_at\": 1707312000000,\n  \"ice_candidates\": [\"1.2.3.4:5000\", \"...\"]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Key Fields Explained:**\n\n| Field | Purpose |\n|-------|---------|\n| `peer_uuid` | Unique identifier for other user |\n| `peer_public_key` | Their encryption key |\n| `content_encrypted` | Store encrypted (for backup) |\n| `content_decrypted` | Store decrypted (for search/display) |\n| `relationship` | `following`, `friend`, `blocked` |\n| `status` | `pending`, `delivered`, `read`, `failed` |\n\n---\n\n**Does this structure look right? Any fields to add/remove?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":956,"output":680,"cacheRead":77888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79524,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770537605742}}
