582   \"created_at\": 1707398400000,\n+583   \"expires_at\": 1708003200000\n+584 }\n+585 ```\n+586 \n 565 ---\n 566 \n+589 ### **Local (Client) Tables — Persistent**\n+590 \n+591 **Purpose:** Full history, source of truth\n+592 \n+593 | Table | Purpose | Storage |\n+594 |-------|---------|---------|\n+595 | **conversations** | Chat metadata | SQLite |\n+596 | **messages** | Message history (encrypted + decrypted) | SQLite |\n+597 | **contacts** | Relationship info | SQLite |\n+598 \n+599 ```json\n+600 // conversations\n+601 {\n+602   \"peer_uuid\": \"def-456\",\n+603   \"peer_public_key\": \"ed25519:xyz...\",\n+604   \"peer_display_name\": \"Bob\",\n+605   \"last_message_at\": 1707312000000,\n+606   \"unread_count\": 3,\n+607   \"relationship\": \"friend\"\n+608 }\n+609 \n+610 // messages\n+611 {\n+612   \"message_id\": \"msg-123\",\n+613   \"conversation_id\": \"def-456\",\n+614   \"sender_uuid\": \"def-456\",\n+615   \"direction\": \"inbound\",\n+616   \"content_encrypted\": \"base64...\",\n+617   \"content_decrypted\": \"Hello!\",\n+618   \"created_at\": 1707312000000,\n+619   \"status\": \"read\"\n+620 }\n+621 \n+622 // contacts\n+623 {\n+624   \"peer_uuid\": \"def-456\",\n+625   \"display_name\": \"Bob\",\n+626   \"public_key\": \"ed25519:xyz...\",\n+627   \"relationship\": \"friend\"\n+628 }\n+629 ```\n+630 \n+631 ---\n+632 \n+633 ### **AI Access Layer**\n+634 \n+635 **Architecture:**\n+636 \n+637 ```\n+638 SQLite (source of truth)\n+639     ↓\n+640 Tool (read_chat)\n+641     ↓\n+642 ┌─────────┴─────────┐\n+643 JSON              MD\n+644 (AI reading)    (backup)\n+645 ```\n+646 \n+647 **Tool Design:**\n+648 \n+649 ```javascript\n+650 // One tool, two output formats\n+651 read_chat({\n+652   conversation: \"alice-uuid\",\n+653   date: \"2026-02-08\",\n+654   format: \"json\"  // or \"md\"\n+655 })\n+656 \n+657 // JSON output (for AI)\n+658 {\"messages\": [{\"time\": \"14:23\", \"sender\": \"alice\", \"content\": \"Hello!\"}]}\n+659 \n+660 // MD output (for backup)\n+661 \"# 2026-02-08\\n\\n## Conversation with Alice\\n\\n**14:23** Hello!\"\n+662 ```\n+663 \n+664 **Why JSON for AI:**\n+665 - Structured, fast to parse\n+666 - Direct field access\n+667 - No markdown parsing needed\n+668 \n+669 **Why MD for backup:**\n+670 - Human-readable\n+671 - Git-friendly\n+672 - Long-term archiving\n+673 \n+674 ---\n+675 \n+676 ### **Backup Strategy**\n+677 \n+678 | Component | What | How |\n+679 |-----------|------|-----|\n+680 | **Primary** | SQLite (chat.db) | Single file, easy backup |\n+681 | **Secondary** | MD files | On-demand export via tool |\n+682 | **Sync** | None needed | MD files generated from DB |\n+683 \n+684 **Context & Discussion:**\n+685 \n+686 > Allan: \"SQLite is source of truth. MD file is built from DB for easier AI access. MD only keeps conversation in real datetime, no timestamp.\" — Feb 8, 2026\n+687 >\n+688 > Allan: \"Tool should export MD format too. One tool, two outputs.\" — Feb 8, 2026\n+689 >\n+690 > Assistant: \"JSON for AI reading (structured), MD for backup (human-readable).\" — Feb 8, 2026\n+691 \n+692 ---\n+693 \n 567 ## 9. API Endpoints\n 568 \n 569 **Function:** What does L2 server expose?\n 570 \n     ...","firstChangedLine":549},"isError":false,"timestamp":1770539779966}}
