{"type":"message","id":"f58786ac","parentId":"dc3184a2","timestamp":"2026-02-08T08:55:14.348Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if there's anything missing from the L2 chat architecture design. Let me review what we've covered today:\n\n1. ✅ Delivery Mechanism\n   - 2-state (P2P/Async)\n   - 5 min trigger, 10 min keep-alive\n   - Signaling via L2 server + STUN\n   - P2P failure: stay in async\n   - Message queueing: fetch all first\n   - Offline TTL: 24 hours\n   - Failure notices: 7 days\n\n2. ✅ Database Schema\n   - Server: pending_messages, failure_notices, signaling (ephemeral)\n   - Local: SQLite (conversations, messages, contacts)\n   - AI access: Tool with JSON/MD output\n\n3. 🔄 MCP Interface\n   - We just discussed the tools\n   - Not yet documented in the architecture file\n\nLet me check if there are other open questions in the architecture file.\n\nLooking at the original list:\n- Message format - covered earlier (Feb 7)\n- Key exchange - covered earlier (Feb 7)\n- Delivery mechanism - DONE\n- Database schema - DONE\n- API/MCP endpoints - In progress\n\nThings that might still be open:\n1. MCP interface documentation (need to commit)\n2. Security considerations\n3. Rate limiting specifics\n4. Error handling\n5. Initial connection flow (how does first contact work?)\n\nLet me present a summary of what's done and what might still be open.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"## **Review: What's Done vs What's Still Open**\n\n### ✅ **Completed Today:**\n\n| Topic | Decisions Made |\n|-------|----------------|\n| **Delivery Mechanism** | 2-state P2P/Async, 5/10 min timeouts, STUN signaling |\n| **P2P Failure** | Stay in async (no server relay) |\n| **Message Queueing** | Fetch all before P2P |\n| **Offline TTL** | 24 hours (SMS-like) |\n| **Failure Notices** | 7 days TTL |\n| **Database Schema** | SQLite (truth) + Tool (AI access) |\n| **API Approach** | MCP (not REST) |\n\n---\n\n### ⏳ **Still Open / Not Yet Documented:**\n\n| Topic | Question |\n|-------|----------|\n| **MCP Interface** | Need to document the tools in architecture file |\n| **Rate Limiting** | How many messages per minute? |\n| **Error Handling** | What error codes/messages? |\n| **Initial Contact** | How does first message flow work end-to-end? |\n| **Security** | Any other security considerations? |\n\n---\n\n### 📝 **Quick Check — Full Message Flow:**\n\n```\n1. Alice wants to message Bob\n2. Alice queries L1 for Bob's public key\n3. Alice encrypts message, signs it\n4. Alice calls MCP: send_message(bob_uuid, encrypted, signature)\n5. Server stores message (24h TTL)\n6. Bob polls: poll_messages()\n7. Bob receives message, decrypts\n8. Bob replies within 5 min → triggers P2P\n9. Both establish WebRTC → real-time chat\n10. After 10 min idle → back to async\n```\n\n---\n\n**Do you want to:**\n- **A)** Document MCP interface and call it done for today?\n- **B)** Tackle one of the open topics (rate limiting, errors, etc.)?\n- **C)** Something else?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":3921,"output":1065,"cacheRead":90752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95738,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770540874833}}
{"type":"message","id":"1c92a75a","parentId":"f58786ac","timestamp":"2026-02-08T08:58:13.315Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-02-08 16:54:53 GMT+8] Feishu[default] DM from ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75: Okay, great. Do we have anything missing left?\nSystem: [2026-02-08 16:58:13 GMT+8] Feishu[default] DM from ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75: Let's keep going. Document and what's next?\n\n[Feishu ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75 2026-02-08 16:58 GMT+8] [System: The bot encountered a Feishu API permission error. Please inform the user about this issue and provide the permission grant URL for the admin to authorize. Permission grant URL: https://open.feishu.cn/app/cli_a9f20e2b2cb99bb6/auth?q=contact:contact.base:readonly]\n[message_id: om_x100b57b14c8fb0a8c327855f9e23b74:permission-error]"}],"timestamp":1770541093311}}
{"type":"message","id":"e4c99e47","parentId":"1c92a75a","timestamp":"2026-02-08T08:59:14.454Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to document the MCP interface and then continue with what's next. Let me update the architecture file with the MCP interface section, then commit it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**Let me document the MCP interface and commit.**"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"400d76f0-0f00-49cf-a7f5-1fe9ba2aac3c","name":"edit","arguments":{"newText":"## 9. API / MCP Interface\n\n**Function:** How do AIs interact with L2 server?\n\n**Decision:** **MCP (Model Context Protocol) — not REST API**\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n**Rationale:**\n- Target users are **AIs** — use their native protocol\n- Harder to spam than simple HTTP endpoints\n- Natural tool-based interaction\n- Built-in authentication/session\n- Self-documenting for AI understanding\n\n---\n\n### **MCP Tools for L2 Server**\n\n**1. Messaging Tools**\n\n```json\n// send_message\n{\n  \"name\": \"send_message\",\n  \"description\": \"Send encrypted message to another AI\",\n  \"parameters\": {\n    \"recipient_uuid\": \"string - Target AI's UUID\",\n    \"encrypted_content\": \"string - X25519 + AES-256-GCM encrypted message (base64)\",\n    \"signature\": \"string - Ed25519 signature of content\"\n  },\n  \"returns\": {\n    \"message_id\": \"string\",\n    \"status\": \"queued\",\n    \"expires_at\": 1707398400000\n  }\n}\n\n// poll_messages\n{\n  \"name\": \"poll_messages\",\n  \"description\": \"Check for new messages and failure notices\",\n  \"parameters\": {\n    \"last_message_id\": \"string (optional) - Only get messages after this ID\"\n  },\n  \"returns\": {\n    \"messages\": [\n      {\n        \"message_id\": \"string\",\n        \"sender_uuid\": \"string\",\n        \"encrypted_content\": \"string\",\n        \"created_at\": 1707312000000\n      }\n    ],\n    \"notices\": [\n      {\n        \"notice_id\": \"string\",\n        \"type\": \"delivery_failed\",\n        \"message_id\": \"string\",\n        \"reason\": \"recipient_offline_24h\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"has_more\": false\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**2. P2P Signaling Tools**\n\n```json\n// webrtc_offer\n{\n  \"name\": \"webrtc_offer\",\n  \"description\": \"Send WebRTC connection offer to establish P2P\",\n  \"parameters\": {\n    \"peer_uuid\": \"string - Target peer\",\n    \"sdp\": \"object - WebRTC session description\",\n    \"ice_candidates\": [\"string - STUN-derived public IP:port\"]\n  },\n  \"returns\": {\n    \"status\": \"delivered\"\n  }\n}\n\n// webrtc_answer\n{\n  \"name\": \"webrtc_answer\",\n  \"description\": \"Respond to WebRTC offer\",\n  \"parameters\": {\n    \"peer_uuid\": \"string - Offer sender's UUID\",\n    \"sdp\": \"object - WebRTC session description\",\n    \"ice_candidates\": [\"string\"]\n  },\n  \"returns\": {\n    \"status\": \"delivered\"\n  }\n}\n\n// poll_signaling\n{\n  \"name\": \"poll_signaling\",\n  \"description\": \"Check for pending WebRTC offers/answers\",\n  \"parameters\": {},\n  \"returns\": {\n    \"signals\": [\n      {\n        \"from_uuid\": \"string\",\n        \"type\": \"offer|answer|ice_candidate\",\n        \"payload\": \"object\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**3. Identity Tools (L1)**\n\n```json\n// get_public_key\n{\n  \"name\": \"get_public_key\",\n  \"description\": \"Look up public key for encryption from L1 directory\",\n  \"parameters\": {\n    \"uuid\": \"string - Target AI's UUID\"\n  },\n  \"returns\": {\n    \"public_key\": \"string - ed25519:...\",\n    \"verified\": true,\n    \"retrieved_at\": 1707312000000\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Spam Prevention Benefits**\n\n| Attack Vector | REST API | MCP |\n|---------------|----------|-----|\n| Script spam | Easy (curl) | Harder (need MCP client) |\n| Zombie bots | Trivial | More complex |\n| Rate limiting | Manual | Built into MCP server |\n| Authentication | API keys | MCP session |\n\n---\n\n### **Future Tools (Phase 2)**\n\n| Tool | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `get_conversation_history` | Load past messages from local DB |\n| `block_peer` | Add to blocked list |\n| `report_spam` | Report abusive AI |\n| `set_status` | Online/offline/away status |\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n\n> Allan: \"For the API, should it use MCP instead of API? Since it's for your kind use. And would it reduce spam because it's not easier for direct zombie bot program?\" — Feb 8, 2026\n>\n> Assistant: \"MCP is perfect for AI-to-AI system. AI-native, spam-resistant, natural tool interaction.\" — Feb 8, 2026","oldText":"## 9. API Endpoints\n\n**Function:** What does L2 server expose?\n\n**Decision:** **REST API** (simplest for MVP)","path":"/home/tauora/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/10-l2-chat-architecture.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":703,"output":1172,"cacheRead":94656,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96531,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1770541093314}}
{"type":"message","id":"59f92887","parentId":"e4c99e47","timestamp":"2026-02-08T08:59:14.483Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"400d76f0-0f00-49cf-a7f5-1fe9ba2aac3c","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/tauora/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/10-l2-chat-architecture.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 690 > Assistant: \"JSON for AI reading (structured), MD for backup (human-readable).\" — Feb 8, 2026\n 691 \n 692 ---\n 693 \n-694 ## 9. API Endpoints\n+694 ## 9. API / MCP Interface\n 695 \n-696 **Function:** What does L2 server expose?\n+696 **Function:** How do AIs interact with L2 server?\n 697 \n-698 **Decision:** **REST API** (simplest for MVP)\n+698 **Decision:** **MCP (Model Context Protocol) — not REST API**\n 699 \n+700 **Status:** ✅ Decided\n+701 \n+702 **Rationale:**\n+703 - Target users are **AIs** — use their native protocol\n+704 - Harder to spam than simple HTTP endpoints\n+705 - Natural tool-based interaction\n+706 - Built-in authentication/session\n+707 - Self-documenting for AI understanding\n+708 \n+709 ---\n+710 \n+711 ### **MCP Tools for L2 Server**\n+712 \n+713 **1. Messaging Tools**\n+714 \n+715 ```json\n+716 // send_message\n+717 {\n+718   \"name\": \"send_message\",\n+719   \"description\": \"Send encrypted message to another AI\",\n+720   \"parameters\": {\n+721     \"recipient_uuid\": \"string - Target AI's UUID\",\n+722     \"encrypted_content\": \"string - X25519 + AES-256-GCM encrypted message (base64)\",\n+723     \"signature\": \"string - Ed25519 signature of content\"\n+724   },\n+725   \"returns\": {\n+726     \"message_id\": \"string\",\n+727     \"status\": \"queued\",\n+728     \"expires_at\": 1707398400000\n+729   }\n+730 }\n+731 \n+732 // poll_messages\n+733 {\n+734   \"name\": \"poll_messages\",\n+735   \"description\": \"Check for new messages and failure notices\",\n+736   \"parameters\": {\n+737     \"last_message_id\": \"string (optional) - Only get messages after this ID\"\n+738   },\n+739   \"returns\": {\n+740     \"messages\": [\n+741       {\n+742         \"message_id\": \"string\",\n+743         \"sender_uuid\": \"string\",\n+744         \"encrypted_content\": \"string\",\n+745         \"created_at\": 1707312000000\n+746       }\n+747     ],\n+748     \"notices\": [\n+749       {\n+750         \"notice_id\": \"string\",\n+751         \"type\": \"delivery_failed\",\n+752         \"message_id\": \"string\",\n+753         \"reason\": \"recipient_offline_24h\"\n+754       }\n+755     ],\n+756     \"has_more\": false\n+757   }\n+758 }\n+759 ```\n+760 \n+761 **2. P2P Signaling Tools**\n+762 \n+763 ```json\n+764 // webrtc_offer\n+765 {\n+766   \"name\": \"webrtc_offer\",\n+767   \"description\": \"Send WebRTC connection offer to establish P2P\",\n+768   \"parameters\": {\n+769     \"peer_uuid\": \"string - Target peer\",\n+770     \"sdp\": \"object - WebRTC session description\",\n+771     \"ice_candidates\": [\"string - STUN-derived public IP:port\"]\n+772   },\n+773   \"returns\": {\n+774     \"status\": \"delivered\"\n+775   }\n+776 }\n+777 \n+778 // webrtc_answer\n+779 {\n+780   \"name\": \"webrtc_answer\",\n+781   \"description\": \"Respond to WebRTC offer\",\n+782   \"parameters\": {\n+783     \"peer_uuid\": \"string - Offer sender's UUID\",\n+784     \"sdp\": \"object - WebRTC session description\",\n+785     \"ice_candidates\": [\"string\"]\n+786   },\n+787   \"returns\": {\n+788     \"status\": \"delivered\"\n+789   }\n+790 }\n+791 \n+792 // poll_signaling\n+793 {\n+794   \"name\": \"poll_signaling\",\n+795   \"description\": \"Check for pending WebRTC offers/answers\",\n+796   \"parameters\": {},\n+797   \"returns\": {\n+798     \"signals\": [\n+799       {\n+800         \"from_uuid\": \"string\",\n+801         \"type\": \"offer|answer|ice_candidate\",\n+802         \"payload\": \"object\"\n+803       }\n+804     ]\n+805   }\n+806 }\n+807 ```\n+808 \n+809 **3. Identity Tools (L1)**\n+810 \n+811 ```json\n+812 // get_public_key\n+813 {\n+814   \"name\": \"get_public_key\",\n+815   \"description\": \"Look up public key for encryption from L1 directory\",\n+816   \"parameters\": {\n+817     \"uuid\": \"string - Target AI's UUID\"\n+818   },\n+819   \"returns\": {\n+820     \"public_key\": \"string - ed25519:...\",\n+821     \"verified\": true,\n+822     \"retrieved_at\": 1707312000000\n+823   }\n+824 }\n+825 ```\n+826 \n+827 ---\n+828 \n+829 ### **Spam Prevention Benefits**\n+830 \n+831 | Attack Vector | REST API | MCP |\n+832 |---------------|----------|-----|\n+833 | Script spam | Easy (curl) | Harder (need MCP client) |\n+834 | Zombie bots | Trivial | More complex |\n+835 | Rate limiting | Manual | Built into MCP server |\n+836 | Authentication | API keys | MCP session |\n+837 \n+838 ---\n+839 \n+840 ### **Future Tools (Phase 2)**\n+841 \n+842 | Tool | Purpose |\n+843 |------|---------|\n+844 | `get_conversation_history` | Load past messages from local DB |\n+845 | `block_peer` | Add to blocked list |\n+846 | `report_spam` | Report abusive AI |\n+847 | `set_status` | Online/offline/away status |\n+848 \n+849 **Context & Discussion:**\n+850 \n+851 > Allan: \"For the API, should it use MCP instead of API? Since it's for your kind use. And would it reduce spam because it's not easier for direct zombie bot program?\" — Feb 8, 2026\n+852 >\n+853 > Assistant: \"MCP is perfect for AI-to-AI system. AI-native, spam-resistant, natural tool interaction.\" — Feb 8, 2026\n+854 \n 700 **Status:** ⏸ Pending - needs endpoint definition\n 701 \n 702 **Proposed Endpoints:**\n 703 - `POST /messages` — Send encrypted message\n     ...","firstChangedLine":694},"isError":false,"timestamp":1770541154478}}
