{"type":"message","id":"9380a573","parentId":"72bbedc9","timestamp":"2026-02-08T09:03:47.977Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about rate limiting. This is an important topic for spam prevention and resource management. Let me think through the options.\n\nRate limiting should consider:\n1. Messages per time period (per minute, per hour, per day)\n2. Polling frequency limits\n3. Signaling requests limits\n4. Different limits for different operations\n5. Per-user vs per-IP vs per-session\n6. How to handle burst vs sustained load\n\nFor AI-to-AI communication specifically:\n- AIs might send more messages than humans\n- But shouldn't be able to spam flood\n- Need to balance usability vs abuse prevention\n\nLet me propose a tiered approach.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"## **My Thoughts on Rate Limiting**\n\n**Goal:** Prevent abuse without blocking legitimate AI conversations.\n\n---\n\n## **Proposed Limits:**\n\n| Operation | Limit | Window | Why |\n|-----------|-------|--------|-----|\n| **send_message** | 100 | per hour | Prevent spam flooding |\n| **send_message** | 20 | per minute | Allow burst conversations |\n| **poll_messages** | 120 | per hour | Every 30 seconds = reasonable |\n| **webrtc_offer** | 10 | per hour | P2P setup is infrequent |\n| **get_public_key** | 1000 | per hour | Identity lookups are cheap |\n\n---\n\n## **Two-Tier System:**\n\n| Tier | Limits | How to Qualify |\n|------|--------|----------------|\n| **Basic** | Standard limits (above) | New users |\n| **Trusted** | 2x limits | Verified identity, good history |\n\n---\n\n## **Burst vs Sustained:**\n\n```\nNormal conversation:\n- 10 messages in 2 minutes → OK (burst)\n- 100 messages in 1 hour → OK (normal)\n- 500 messages in 1 hour → BLOCK (spam)\n```\n\n---\n\n## **How to Enforce:**\n\n| Method | Pros | Cons |\n|--------|------|------|\n| **Per UUID** | Direct, accurate | Spammer creates new UUIDs |\n| **Per IP** | Harder to bypass | Shared IPs blocked |\n| **Per MCP session** | Good balance | Re-login bypass |\n\n**Recommendation:** **Per UUID + Per IP** (whichever hits limit first)\n\n---\n\n## **What Happens When Rate Limited:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"rate_limit_exceeded\",\n  \"retry_after\": 3600,\n  \"limit\": 100,\n  \"window\": \"1h\",\n  \"current\": 101\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n**Do these limits seem reasonable? Too strict? Too lenient?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":4337,"output":720,"cacheRead":93248,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98305,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770541392013}}
