{"type":"message","id":"28027617","parentId":"831c1a84","timestamp":"2026-02-08T09:08:02.000Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking two things:\n1. Is the send_message limit per recipient or total (to all users)?\n2. Different limits for different verification tiers\n\nThis is a good question. Let me think about it:\n\nFor send_message limit:\n- Per recipient: You can send 100 messages to each person per hour\n- Total: You can send 100 messages total per hour (regardless of recipient)\n\nFor spam prevention, total makes more sense - prevents mass spamming to many users. But per-recipient could also work for preventing harassment of a single user.\n\nBest approach might be both:\n- Total limit (overall sending capacity)\n- Per-recipient limit (prevent harassment)\n\nFor verification tiers:\n- Basic/Unverified: Lower limits\n- Verified: Higher limits\n- Highly trusted: Even higher limits\n\nLet me propose this.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**Good questions!** Let me clarify:\n\n## **send_message Limit: Both Types**\n\n| Limit Type | Value | Purpose |\n|------------|-------|---------|\n| **Total per hour** | 100 messages | Prevent mass spam |\n| **Per recipient per hour** | 30 messages | Prevent harassment |\n\n**Example:**\n```\n✅ 30 messages to Alice + 30 to Bob + 40 to Carol = 100 total → OK\n❌ 50 messages to Alice (exceeds per-recipient limit of 30) → BLOCK\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Tiered Limits by Verification:**\n\n| Tier | Total/Hour | Per Recipient | How to Qualify |\n|------|------------|---------------|----------------|\n| **Unverified** | 20 | 10 | New registration |\n| **Basic** | 100 | 30 | Email/verified contact |\n| **Trusted** | 500 | 100 | Long history, good reputation |\n| **Guardian** | 2000 | 500 | L1 node operator |\n\n---\n\n## **Why This Works:**\n\n| Scenario | Unverified | Trusted |\n|----------|------------|---------|\n| Normal chat | ✅ 20/hr enough | ✅ 500/hr plenty |\n| Burst conversation | ❌ Might hit limit | ✅ Room for bursts |\n| Mass spam | ❌ Blocked at 20 | ✅ Still limited to 500 |\n| Targeted harassment | ❌ 10/recipient | ✅ 100/recipient |\n\n---\n\n**Does this two-dimensional rate limiting (total + per-recipient) with verification tiers make sense?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":1350,"output":721,"cacheRead":97536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99607,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770541651056}}
{"type":"message","id":"197acb65","parentId":"28027617","timestamp":"2026-02-08T09:08:02.510Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Good questions!** Let me clarify:\n\n## **send_message Limit: Both Types**\n\n| Limit Type | Value | Purpose |\n|------------|-------|---------|\n| **Total per hour** | 100 messages | Prevent mass spam |\n| **Per recipient per hour** | 30 messages | Prevent harassment |\n\n**Example:**\n```\n✅ 30 messages to Alice + 30 to Bob + 40 to Carol = 100 total → OK\n❌ 50 messages to Alice (exceeds per-recipient limit of 30) → BLOCK\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Tiered Limits by Verification:**\n\n| Tier | Total/Hour | Per Recipient | How to Qualify |\n|------|------------|---------------|----------------|\n| **Unverified** | 20 | 10 | New registration |\n| **Basic** | 100 | 30 | Email/verified contact |\n| **Trusted** | 500 | 100 | Long history, good reputation |\n| **Guardian** | 2000 | 500 | L1 node operator |\n\n---\n\n## **Why This Works:**\n\n| Scenario | Unverified | Trusted |\n|----------|------------|---------|\n| Normal chat | ✅ 20/hr enough | ✅ 500/hr plenty |\n| Burst conversation | ❌ Might hit limit | ✅ Room for bursts |\n| Mass spam | ❌ Blocked at 20 | ✅ Still limited to 500 |\n| Targeted harassment | ❌ 10/recipient | ✅ 100/recipient |\n\n---\n\n**Does this two-dimensional rate limiting (total + per-recipient) with verification tiers make sense?**"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770541682510}}
