{"type":"message","id":"db720392","parentId":"5111c6f6","timestamp":"2026-02-08T09:18:30.762Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is pointing out more factors to consider for rate limiting:\n\n1. **Relationships matter:**\n   - Friends should have higher limits (trusted)\n   - Strangers should have lower limits (caution)\n   - Blocked = 0 messages allowed\n\n2. **Async vs P2P matters:**\n   - Async (server-relayed) should have stricter limits (server load)\n   - P2P (direct connection) can be unlimited (no server involvement)\n\nThis is a great insight. Let me update the rate limiting design to incorporate these factors.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**Excellent points!** Let me expand the rate limiting design:\n\n## **Rate Limiting Factors:**\n\n| Factor | Impact on Limit |\n|--------|-----------------|\n| **Verification tier** | Higher tier = higher limit |\n| **Relationship** | Friends > Strangers > Blocked |\n| **Connection type** | P2P (unlimited) > Async (limited) |\n\n---\n\n## **Relationship-Based Limits:**\n\n| Relationship | Async Limit | P2P Limit |\n|--------------|-------------|-----------|\n| **Friend** | 500/hour | Unlimited |\n| **Following** | 100/hour | Unlimited |\n| **Stranger** | 10/hour | Unlimited |\n| **Blocked** | 0 | 0 |\n\n---\n\n## **Complete Rate Limit Table:**\n\n| Tier | Relationship | Async Total | Async Per Recipient | P2P |\n|------|--------------|-------------|---------------------|-----|\n| **Unverified** | Friend | 100 | 50 | Unlimited |\n| | Stranger | 5 | 5 | Unlimited |\n| **Basic** | Friend | 300 | 100 | Unlimited |\n| | Stranger | 20 | 10 | Unlimited |\n| **Trusted** | Friend | 1000 | 300 | Unlimited |\n| | Stranger | 100 | 30 | Unlimited |\n| **Guardian** | All | 2000 | 500 | Unlimited |\n\n---\n\n## **Why P2P is Unlimited:**\n\n- No server load (direct connection)\n- Both parties agreed to connect\n- Connection drops = back to async (limits apply)\n\n---\n\n## **Blocked = 0 Always:**\n\n```\nBlocked relationship:\n- Async: Rejected immediately\n- P2P: Connection refused\n- No notifications sent to sender\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Key Insight:**\n\n| Scenario | Limit Applied |\n|----------|---------------|\n| **First contact (stranger)** | Strict (10/hour) |\n| **Accepted friend** | Relaxed (500/hour) |\n| **P2P established** | Unlimited (no server) |\n| **Blocked** | Zero |\n\n**Does this relationship-aware + connection-aware rate limiting make sense?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":93498,"output":698,"cacheRead":6272,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100468,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770542276041}}
