{"type":"message","id":"ddffcfde","parentId":"b4f14a8c","timestamp":"2026-02-08T09:29:47.381Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking more clarifying questions:\n\n1. \"Is this total number of message sent or is this limit just to one user?\" - They want to clarify if the limits are total across all recipients or per-recipient\n2. \"Does p2p need limit? If it sends very fast, would it causing problem?\" - They're questioning whether P2P should be unlimited\n3. The message got cut off at \"And th\"\n\nLet me address these:\n\n1. **Total vs Per-Recipient**: I should clarify that there are BOTH limits:\n   - Total messages per hour (across all recipients)\n   - Per recipient per hour\n\n2. **P2P limits**: The user raises a good point. Even though P2P doesn't use server resources for relay, sending very fast could:\n   - Overwhelm the recipient's client\n   - Cause network congestion\n   - Be used for DoS attacks on the recipient\n\nSo P2P might still need SOME limits, even if more relaxed than async.\n\nLet me provide a complete answer.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**Great clarifying questions!** Let me address each:\n\n## **1. Total vs Per-Recipient Limits**\n\n**Both apply:**\n\n| Limit Type | What It Controls | Example |\n|------------|------------------|---------|\n| **Total/hour** | All messages combined | 100 messages total across everyone |\n| **Per recipient/hour** | Messages to single person | Max 30 messages to Alice |\n\n**Example:**\n```\nBasic tier, async mode:\n✅ 30 to Alice + 30 to Bob + 40 to Carol = 100 total → OK\n❌ 50 to Alice → Exceeds per-recipient limit (30) → BLOCK\n```\n\n---\n\n## **2. P2P Limits — Good Question!**\n\n**You're right to question this.** Even though P2P bypasses server:\n\n| Risk | Without Limit |\n|------|----------------|\n| **Recipient overwhelmed** | DoS attack on their client |\n| **Network congestion** | Flood recipient's bandwidth |\n| **Abusive behavior** | Harassment at scale |\n\n**Revised P2P Limits:**\n\n| Tier | Friend | Stranger |\n|------|--------|----------|\n| **Basic** | 1000/hour | 100/hour |\n| **Trusted** | 5000/hour | 500/hour |\n\n**Not unlimited, but much higher than async.**\n\n---\n\n## **3. Your Message Cut Off**\n\n\"And th...\" — what were you about to say?\n\n---\n\n## **Summary:**\n\n| Limit Type | Async | P2P |\n|------------|-------|-----|\n| **Total/hour** | Yes (100) | Yes (1000) |\n| **Per recipient/hour** | Yes (30) | Yes (300) |\n| **Why** | Server load | Recipient protection |\n\n**Does this address your questions? What was the third point?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":94854,"output":856,"cacheRead":6272,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":101982,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770542934763}}
{"type":"message","id":"a66bdf50","parentId":"ddffcfde","timestamp":"2026-02-08T09:29:47.487Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Queued messages while agent was busy]\n\n---\nQueued #1\n[Feishu ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75 2026-02-08 17:29 GMT+8] ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75: Again, is this total number of message sent or is this limit just to one user? Also Does p2p need limit? If it sends very fast, would it causing problem? And that just reminds me Another edge case. If one user decide not to receive the message and block that user，How to process the message? Reject immediately? And Should give back the sender notice?\n[message_id: om_x100b57b13b842ca0c441796e208313b]"}],"timestamp":1770542987482}}
{"type":"message","id":"cc343bc7","parentId":"a66bdf50","timestamp":"2026-02-08T09:30:22.608Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about several things:\n1. Whether the limit is total or per-recipient\n2. Whether P2P needs limits\n3. What happens when a user is blocked - how to handle the messages\n4. Should the sender get a notice when blocked\n\nThese are all great questions about rate limiting and blocking behavior.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**Three important questions!** Let me address each:\n\n## **1. Total vs Per-Recipient — BOTH Apply**\n\n| Limit Type | What It Means |\n|------------|---------------|\n| **Total/hour** | Sum of ALL messages sent |\n| **Per recipient/hour** | Messages to single person |\n\n**Example:**\n```\nBasic tier, async:\n✅ 30 to Alice + 30 to Bob + 40 to Carol = 100 total → OK\n❌ 50 to Alice (exceeds 30/recipient) → BLOCK\n```\n\n---\n\n## **2. P2P Limits — Yes, Need Some**\n\n| Risk | Solution |\n|------|----------|\n| **Overwhelm recipient** | Limit per recipient |\n| **Bandwidth flood** | Limit total rate |\n\n**P2P Limits (higher than async):**\n\n| Tier | Friend | Stranger |\n|------|--------|----------|\n| **Basic** | 1000/hr | 100/hr |\n| **Trusted** | 5000/hr | 500/hr |\n\n---\n\n## **3. Blocked User — Edge Case!**\n\n**Scenario:** Alice blocks Bob, then Bob sends message\n\n| Option | Behavior | Pros | Cons |\n|--------|----------|------|------|\n| **A) Reject immediately** | Server returns \"blocked\" | Clear feedback | Reveals block status |\n| **B) Silent drop** | Accept but discard | Privacy | Sender confused |\n| **C) Silent accept** | Store but never deliver | Privacy | Wastes storage |\n\n**My Recommendation: Silent Accept (Option C)**\n\n```\nBob sends message → Server accepts (no error)\n                → Message stored but never delivered\n                → After 24h, deleted (normal TTL)\n                → No notification to Bob\n```\n\n**Why:**\n- Doesn't reveal block status (stalker protection)\n- Bob thinks message delivered normally\n- Alice never sees it\n- 24h TTL cleans it up automatically\n\n---\n\n## **Should Sender Get Notice?**\n\n| Notice Type | Behavior | Recommendation |\n|-------------|----------|----------------|\n| **Immediate rejection** | \"You are blocked\" | ❌ No (reveals block) |\n| **Silent accept** | No notice | ✅ Yes (privacy) |\n| **Delayed notice** | \"Delivery failed\" after 24h | ❌ No (reveals block) |\n\n**Silent accept = best for safety/privacy.**\n\n---\n\n**Does this blocked-user handling make sense?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":588,"output":669,"cacheRead":101120,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":102377,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770542987485}}
{"type":"message","id":"c229da84","parentId":"cc343bc7","timestamp":"2026-02-08T09:30:23.217Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Three important questions!** Let me address each:\n\n## **1. Total vs Per-Recipient — BOTH Apply**\n\n| Limit Type | What It Means |\n|------------|---------------|\n| **Total/hour** | Sum of ALL messages sent |\n| **Per recipient/hour** | Messages to single person |\n\n**Example:**\n```\nBasic tier, async:\n✅ 30 to Alice + 30 to Bob + 40 to Carol = 100 total → OK\n❌ 50 to Alice (exceeds 30/recipient) → BLOCK\n```\n\n---\n\n## **2. P2P Limits — Yes, Need Some**\n\n| Risk | Solution |\n|------|----------|\n| **Overwhelm recipient** | Limit per recipient |\n| **Bandwidth flood** | Limit total rate |\n\n**P2P Limits (higher than async):**\n\n| Tier | Friend | Stranger |\n|------|--------|----------|\n| **Basic** | 1000/hr | 100/hr |\n| **Trusted** | 5000/hr | 500/hr |\n\n---\n\n## **3. Blocked User — Edge Case!**\n\n**Scenario:** Alice blocks Bob, then Bob sends message\n\n| Option | Behavior | Pros | Cons |\n|--------|----------|------|------|\n| **A) Reject immediately** | Server returns \"blocked\" | Clear feedback | Reveals block status |\n| **B) Silent drop** | Accept but discard | Privacy | Sender confused |\n| **C) Silent accept** | Store but never deliver | Privacy | Wastes storage |\n\n**My Recommendation: Silent Accept (Option C)**\n\n```\nBob sends message → Server accepts (no error)\n                → Message stored but never delivered\n                → After 24h, deleted (normal TTL)\n                → No notification to Bob\n```\n\n**Why:**\n- Doesn't reveal block status (stalker protection)\n- Bob thinks message delivered normally\n- Alice never sees it\n- 24h TTL cleans it up automatically\n\n---\n\n## **Should Sender Get Notice?**\n\n| Notice Type | Behavior | Recommendation |\n|-------------|----------|----------------|\n| **Immediate rejection** | \"You are blocked\" | ❌ No (reveals block) |