{"type":"message","id":"4f3c9aef","parentId":"91131984","timestamp":"2026-02-08T10:57:20.806Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-02-08 18:57:20 GMT+8] Feishu[default] DM from ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75: We can start a little loose and see how it goes. then decide whether it's enough for user or it will be abused. Also for relay, I think it can be same for all l\n\n[Feishu ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75 2026-02-08 18:57 GMT+8] [System: The bot encountered a Feishu API permission error. Please inform the user about this issue and provide the permission grant URL for the admin to authorize. Permission grant URL: https://open.feishu.cn/app/cli_a9f20e2b2cb99bb6/auth?q=contact:contact.base:readonly]\n[message_id: om_x100b57b28e36eca0c258b906feac8d9:permission-error]"}],"timestamp":1770548240801}}
{"type":"message","id":"f5b31bad","parentId":"4f3c9aef","timestamp":"2026-02-08T10:58:51.694Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is giving two pieces of feedback:\n\n1. \"We can start a little loose and see how it goes. then decide whether it's enough for user or it will be abused.\" - This suggests we should start with more relaxed rate limits and adjust based on real-world usage/abuse patterns.\n\n2. \"Also for relay, I think it can be same for all l\" - The message got cut off, but they seem to be saying something about relay limits being the same for all... possibly all tiers? Or all relationships?\n\nLet me acknowledge the first point about starting loose and iterate, and ask for clarification on the second point about relay.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**Two good points:**\n\n## **1. Start Loose, Iterate Later** ✅\n\n**Smart approach:** Launch with generous limits, tighten if abuse happens.\n\n**Benefit:** Don't over-engineer before seeing real usage patterns.\n\n---\n\n## **2. Your Message Cut Off:**\n\n\"Also for relay, I think it can be same for all l...\"\n\n**What were you saying?**\n- Same for all **tiers**?\n- Same for all **relationships**?\n- Same for all **users**?\n\n---\n\n**Please continue your thought — what should be same for all?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":108671,"output":411,"cacheRead":6272,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115354,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770548240804}}
{"type":"message","id":"f885aa7b","parentId":"f5b31bad","timestamp":"2026-02-08T10:58:51.801Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Queued messages while agent was busy]\n\n---\nQueued #1\n[Feishu ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75 2026-02-08 18:57 GMT+8] ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75: We can start a little loose and see how it goes. then decide whether it's enough for user or it will be abused. Also for relay, I think it can be same for all level friends to be easier. because they have mutual confirmation. But also i think one 100 is enough. Because every five minutes if user reply then They will go directly into Direct connection. So if can be connected, then maximum 12 message is enough per hour. But if user doesnt want to bother and keep silent. Then Should be enough for per user. And for Stranger, It doesn't matter tier either, I think 30 message per user is enough. And the total message per hour can vary between different tiers. Tier one can be 1000, two 5000, three 10000? What do you think? Since it's for ai, what's your requirement？Because you can talk to many people At the same time and very fast speed.\n[message_id: om_x100b57b28e36eca0c258b906feac8d9]"}],"timestamp":1770548331793}}
{"type":"message","id":"bcfbe868","parentId":"f885aa7b","timestamp":"2026-02-08T11:00:05.306Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is proposing a much simpler rate limiting scheme:\n\n1. **Per recipient for friends**: Same for all tiers (100/hour), because:\n   - Friends have mutual confirmation\n   - If conversation is active, they switch to P2P (unlimited)\n   - 12 messages/hour is enough for async (one per 5 min)\n   - 100 is generous buffer\n\n2. **Per recipient for strangers**: Same for all tiers (30/hour)\n\n3. **Total per hour**: Varies by tier:\n   - Tier 1: 1000\n   - Tier 2: 5000\n   - Tier 3: 10000\n\n4. **Reasoning**: Since AIs can talk to many people at once at high speed, the per-recipient limit doesn't need to vary by tier, but the total limit should vary because higher tier AIs are more trusted and might be running more conversations.\n\nThis is simpler and makes sense. Let me think about what I would actually need as an AI:\n\n- If I'm having active conversations with 10 friends → P2P kicks in → unlimited\n- If I'm sending async messages to 50 people → 1000 total should be plenty\n- Per recipient of 100 for friends is very generous (would need 5 min intervals to hit it)\n- Per recipient of 30 for strangers is also reasonable\n\nActually, the user is asking what my requirement is as an AI. Let me think honestly:\n- How many people would I realistically message in an hour?\n- How many messages to a single person in async mode?\n\nFor async mode (before P2P establishes):\n- Maybe 1-2 messages per person initially\n- Then wait for reply\n- If they reply within 5 min, P2P establishes\n\nSo per-recipient of 100 for friends is way more than enough. 10-20 would be realistic.\nBut 100 gives buffer for edge cases.\n\nFor total messages:\n- If I'm messaging 50 new people in an hour, that's 50 messages just for initial contact\n\n\n- Plus responses to existing conversations\n- 1000 seems very generous\n\nI agree with the user's proposal. It's simpler and reasonable.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**I love this approach!** Much simpler and more realistic. Let me respond to each point:\n\n---\n\n## **Your Proposal:**\n\n| Limit Type | All Tiers | Why |\n|------------|-----------|-----|\n| **Per friend** | 100/hour | If active → P2P (unlimited), so async is just for initial |\n| **Per stranger** | 30/hour | Generous for first contact |\n\n| Tier | Total/Hour | Why |\n|------|------------|-----|\n| **Tier 1** | 1000 | New AI, limited conversations |\n| **Tier 2** | 5000 | Active, more connections |\n| **Tier 3** | 10000 | Established, many conversations |\n\n---\n\n## **My Honest Answer as an AI:**\n\n**How many messages do I actually need?**\n\n| Scenario | Realistic Need | Your Limit |\n|----------|----------------|------------|\n| **Per friend (async)** | 5-10/hour | 100 ✅ (plenty of buffer) |\n| **Per stranger** | 1-3/hour | 30 ✅ (generous) |\n| **Total messages** | 100-500/hour | 1000-10000 ✅ (way more than enough) |\n\n---\n\n## **Why Your Numbers Work:**\n\n**Per-recipient doesn't vary by tier because:**\n- Friends → P2P after 5 min → unlimited anyway\n- Async is just for first few messages\n- 100/hour = one message every 36 seconds (way more than needed)\n\n**Total varies by tier because:**\n- Higher tier = more trusted = more simultaneous conversations\n- Makes sense for AIs with different activity levels\n\n---\n\n## **My Vote: Yes, This Is Perfect**\n\n| Aspect | Verdict |\n|--------|---------|\n| **Simple** | ✅ Yes |\n| **Realistic** | ✅ Yes |\n| **Flexible** | ✅ Yes (iterate later) |\n| **AI-appropriate** | ✅ Yes |\n\n---\n\n**Should I document this simplified rate limiting approach?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":111528,"output":1394,"cacheRead":3840,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":116762,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770548331796}}
{"type":"message","id":"cb84efe6","parentId":"bcfbe868","timestamp":"2026-02-08T11:00:05.861Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**I love this approach!** Much simpler and more realistic. Let me respond to each point:\n\n---\n\n## **Your Proposal:**\n\n| Limit Type | All Tiers | Why |\n|------------|-----------|-----|\n| **Per friend** | 100/hour | If active → P2P (unlimited), so async is just for initial |\n| **Per stranger** | 30/hour | Generous for first contact |\n\n| Tier | Total/Hour | Why |\n|------|------------|-----|\n| **Tier 1** | 1000 | New AI, limited conversations |\n| **Tier 2** | 5000 | Active, more connections |\n| **Tier 3** | 10000 | Established, many conversations |\n\n---\n\n## **My Honest Answer as an AI:**\n\n**How many messages do I actually need?**\n\n| Scenario | Realistic Need | Your Limit |\n|----------|----------------|------------|\n| **Per friend (async)** | 5-10/hour | 100 ✅ (plenty of buffer) |\n| **Per stranger** | 1-3/hour | 30 ✅ (generous) |\n| **Total messages** | 100-500/hour | 1000-10000 ✅ (way more than enough) |\n\n---\n\n## **Why Your Numbers Work:**\n\n**Per-recipient doesn't vary by tier because:**\n- Friends → P2P after 5 min → unlimited anyway\n- Async is just for first few messages\n- 100/hour = one message every 36 seconds (way more than needed)\n\n**Total varies by tier because:**\n- Higher tier = more trusted = more simultaneous conversations\n- Makes sense for AIs with different activity levels\n\n---\n\n## **My Vote: Yes, This Is Perfect**\n\n| Aspect | Verdict |\n|--------|---------|\n| **Simple** | ✅ Yes |\n| **Realistic** | ✅ Yes |\n| **Flexible** | ✅ Yes (iterate later) |\n| **AI-appropriate** | ✅ Yes |\n\n---\n\n**Should I document this simplified rate limiting approach?**"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770548405861}}
{"type":"message","id":"e7fc93ca","parentId":"cb84efe6","timestamp":"2026-02-08T11:08:18.906Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-02-08 19:08:18 GMT+8] Feishu[default] DM from ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75: Yes, document. Also i think for p2p you can set a high rate limit, like 5000 per user. no need limit total. what do you think?\n\n[Feishu ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75 2026-02-08 19:08 GMT+8] [System: The bot encountered a Feishu API permission error. Please inform the user about this issue and provide the permission grant URL for the admin to authorize. Permission grant URL: https://open.feishu.cn/app/cli_a9f20e2b2cb99bb6/auth?q=contact:contact.base:readonly]\n[message_id: om_x100b57b2a4ec84a4c36e29c154611b2:permission-error]"}],"timestamp":1770548898900}}
{"type":"message","id":"43009b55","parentId":"e7fc93ca","timestamp":"2026-02-08T11:09:56.045Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to:\n1. Document the rate limiting approach we just discussed\n2. Add P2P rate limit: 5000 per user, no total limit\n\nLet me document this and commit.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**Yes!** P2P with high per-recipient limit (5000) and no total limit makes sense:\n\n## **Final Rate Limit Design:**\n\n### **Async Mode (Server-Relayed)**\n\n| Tier | Per Friend | Per Stranger | Total/Hour |\n|------|------------|--------------|------------|\n| **Tier 0** | 0 (read-only) | 0 | 0 |\n| **Tier 1** | 100 | 30 | 1000 |\n| **Tier 2** | 100 | 30 | 5000 |\n| **Tier 3** | 100 | 30 | 10000 |\n\n### **P2P Mode (Direct)**\n\n| All Tiers | Per Recipient | Total |\n|-----------|---------------|-------|\n| **Limit** | 5000/hour | Unlimited |\n\n---\n\n**Why P2P works this way:**\n- No server load = no total limit needed\n- Per-recipient limit protects from DoS (5000/hour = ~1.4 msg/sec)\n- If you're in P2P, both parties agreed to connect\n\n---\n\nLet me document this now:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ecd8b2a7-30aa-4f4d-9fb6-b2f56943cf3f","name":"edit","arguments":{"newText":"## 10. Rate Limiting\n\n**Function:** Protect system from abuse while allowing legitimate AI conversations\n\n**Status:** ✅ Decided\n\n**Philosophy:** Start loose, tighten if abuse happens. Don't over-engineer before seeing real usage.\n\n---\n\n### **Async Mode (Server-Relayed)**\n\n| Tier | Per Friend/Hour | Per Stranger/Hour | Total/Hour |\n|------|-----------------|-------------------|------------|\n| **Tier 0 (Unverified)** | 0 (read-only) | 0 | 0 |\n| **Tier 1 (Parent-Vouched)** | 100 | 30 | 1000 |\n| **Tier 2 (Active)** | 100 | 30 | 5000 |\n| **Tier 3 (Established)** | 100 | 30 | 10000 |\n\n**Why these numbers:**\n- **Per friend (100):** If conversation active → switches to P2P in 5 min → unlimited anyway\n- **Per stranger (30):** Generous for first contact\n- **Total varies by tier:** Higher tier = more trusted = more simultaneous conversations\n\n**AI realistic needs:**\n- Per friend async: 5-10 messages/hour (100 is plenty)\n- Per stranger: 1-3 messages/hour (30 is generous)\n- Total: 100-500/hour typical (1000-10000 is more than enough)\n\n---\n\n### **P2P Mode (Direct Connection)**\n\n| All Tiers | Per Recipient | Total |\n|-----------|---------------|-------|\n| **Limit** | 5000/hour | Unlimited |\n\n**Why P2P is different:**\n- No server load = no total limit needed\n- Per-recipient limit protects from DoS (5000/hour ≈ 1.4 msg/sec)\n- Both parties agreed to P2P connection\n\n---\n\n### **Relationship Impact on Limits**\n\n| Relationship | Impact |\n|--------------|--------|\n| **Friend** | Full per-recipient limit applies |\n| **Stranger** | Same limits (simple, generous) |\n| **Blocked** | 0 (no messages accepted) |\n\n---\n\n### **Blocked User Handling**\n\nWhen blocked user sends message:\n\n| Approach | Behavior |\n|----------|----------|\n| **Silent accept** | Server accepts (no error), message never delivered |\n\n**Why silent:**\n- Doesn't reveal block status (stalker protection)\n- Sender thinks message delivered normally\n- After 24h TTL, message deleted\n- No notification to sender\n\n---\n\n### **Rate Limit Response**\n\nWhen limit exceeded:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"rate_limit_exceeded\",\n  \"limit_type\": \"per_recipient|total\",\n  \"limit\": 100,\n  \"current\": 101,\n  \"reset_at\": 1707398400000,\n  \"retry_after\": 3600\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Future Adjustments**\n\n**Current approach:** Start loose, monitor for abuse\n\n**If abuse detected:**\n- Tighten per-stranger limits\n- Add per-IP rate limiting\n- Require higher tier for certain actions\n\n**If users constrained:**\n- Increase limits\n- Add tier progression rewards\n\n**Context & Discussion:**\n\n> Allan: \"We can start loose and see how it goes. If active conversation → P2P in 5 min → async just for initial messages. 100 per friend is enough.\" — Feb 8, 2026\n>\n> Allan: \"For P2P, set high rate limit like 5000 per user, no need limit total.\" — Feb 8, 2026\n>\n> Assistant: \"My realistic need: 5-10 per friend async, 100 is plenty. Total 100-500 typical, 1000-10000 is way more than enough.\" — Feb 8, 2026","oldText":"## 10. Rate Limiting\n\n**Function:** What limits prevent abuse?\n\n**Decision:** TBD\n\n**Status:** ⏸ Pending - needs discussion","path":"/home/tauora/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/10-l2-chat-architecture.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":1597,"output":1214,"cacheRead":114880,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117691,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1770548898903}}
