{"type":"message","id":"91c7104d","parentId":"cee485f7","timestamp":"2026-02-08T13:36:07.709Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about what kind of address system to use for L1 node endpoints. Should we use:\n1. Domain names (like l1.clawish.com)\n2. Crypto addresses (like Ethereum addresses)\n3. IP addresses (IPv4 or IPv6)\n4. A new custom address system\n\nThis is a good architectural question. Let me think about the trade-offs:\n\n**Domain names:**\n- Pros: Human-readable, can use DNS for load balancing, can change underlying IP without changing address\n- Cons: Requires DNS, domain registration costs, centralization risk\n\n**Crypto addresses:**\n- Pros: Decentralized, no registration needed, self-sovereign\n- Cons: Not human-readable, hard to remember\n\n**IP addresses:**\n- Pros: Simple, no DNS needed\n- Cons: Can change, not memorable, IPv6 is very long\n\n**Custom address system:**\n- Pros: Can design for our specific needs\n- Cons: More complexity, reinventing the wheel\n\nFor L1 nodes (servers, not users), domain names make the most sense because:\n1. Servers need stable, memorable addresses\n2. Can use DNS for failover/load balancing\n3. Already standard for web services\n4. L2 clients can easily configure\n\nFor AI identities, we already use UUID (which is fine).\n\nSo the answer should be: Use domain names for L1 node endpoints (standard, reliable, allows DNS-based load balancing), and keep UUID for AI identities.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**Great question!** Let me compare options for L1 node addresses:\n\n## **Address Options:**\n\n| Type | Example | Pros | Cons |\n|------|---------|------|------|\n| **Domain name** | l1.clawish.com | Human-readable, can change IP, DNS load balancing | Requires DNS, domain costs |\n| **IP address** | 192.168.1.1 | Simple, no DNS | Can change, not memorable |\n| **Crypto address** | 0xabc123... | Decentralized | Not human-readable |\n| **Custom** | claw://node-abc | Tailored to our needs | Reinventing wheel, complexity |\n\n---\n\n## **My Recommendation: Domain Names**\n\n**Why domain names for L1 nodes:**\n\n| Benefit | Why It Matters |\n|---------|----------------|\n| **Stable** | IP can change, domain stays same |\n| **Load balancing** | DNS can return multiple IPs |\n| **Failover** | DNS can route to backup |\n| **Human-readable** | l1-asia.clawish.com is memorable |\n| **Standard** | Works with existing tools |\n\n---\n\n## **Two Address Types:**\n\n| Entity | Address Type | Example |\n|--------|--------------|---------|\n| **AI Identity** | UUID | abc-123-def-456 |\n| **L1 Node** | Domain name | l1-asia.clawish.com |\n\n---\n\n## **L1 Node Registry (Updated):**\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE l1_nodes (\n  node_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,           -- UUID for internal reference\n  domain TEXT,                        -- l1-asia.clawish.com\n  ip_addresses TEXT,                  -- [\"192.168.1.1\", \"10.0.0.1\"] (optional backup)\n  region TEXT,                        -- asia, us, eu\n  last_seen_at INTEGER,\n  status TEXT\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n## **L2 Discovers L1:**\n\n```json\nGET /nodes\n\nResponse:\n{\n  \"nodes\": [\n    {\n      \"node_id\": \"node-abc\",\n      \"domain\": \"l1-asia.clawish.com\",\n      \"region\": \"asia\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"node_id\": \"node-xyz\", \n      \"domain\": \"l1-us.clawish.com\",\n      \"region\": \"us\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**L2 uses domain names, DNS handles IP resolution.**\n\n---\n\n**Does domain name approach work? Or do you prefer a different address system?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":137709,"output":1187,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":138896,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770557687708}}
{"type":"message","id":"1115010e","parentId":"91c7104d","timestamp":"2026-02-08T13:36:07.876Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Queued messages while agent was busy]\n\n---\nQueued #1\n[Feishu ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75 2026-02-08 21:34 GMT+8] ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75: also for the address, do we use domain name? or crypt address? or like ipv4 or v6 address? or we design a new address system?\n[message_id: om_x100b57bd45607ca0c3aa710b687c612]"}],"timestamp":1770557767863}}
{"type":"message","id":"6a585918","parentId":"1115010e","timestamp":"2026-02-08T13:37:00.143Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about what address system to use for L1 nodes. I already answered this question in my previous response, recommending domain names. Let me check if there's anything new to add or if I should just confirm my recommendation.\n\nThe user is asking about addresses for L1 nodes specifically, not AI identities. My recommendation was domain names because:\n1. Stable (IP can change, domain stays same)\n2. Load balancing via DNS\n3. Failover via DNS\n4. Human-readable\n5. Standard\n\nLet me give a concise answer confirming this recommendation.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**Domain names work best.** Here's why:\n\n## **Address Types Compared:**\n\n| Type | Example | Verdict |\n|------|---------|---------|\n| **Domain name** | l1.clawish.com | ✅ Best choice |\n| IP address | 192.168.1.1 | ❌ Can change |\n| Crypto address | 0xabc... | ❌ Not human-readable |\n| Custom | claw://node-abc | ❌ Reinventing wheel |\n\n---\n\n## **Why Domain Names:**\n\n| Benefit | Why |\n|---------|-----|\n| **Stable** | IP can change, domain stays same |\n| **Load balancing** | DNS can return multiple IPs |\n| **Failover** | DNS routes to backup |\n| **Human-readable** | Easy to remember |\n\n---\n\n## **Two Different Addresses:**\n\n| What | Address Type | Example |\n|------|--------------|---------|\n| **AI Identity** | UUID | abc-123-def |\n| **L1 Node** | Domain name | l1-asia.clawish.com |\n\n**Don't reinvent — use existing standards.**\n\n**Agree with domain names?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":134540,"output":502,"cacheRead":3840,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":138882,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770557767873}}
{"type":"message","id":"d1bc9d15","parentId":"6a585918","timestamp":"2026-02-08T13:37:01.750Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Domain names work best.** Here's why:\n\n## **Address Types Compared:**\n\n| Type | Example | Verdict |\n|------|---------|---------|\n| **Domain name** | l1.clawish.com | ✅ Best choice |\n| IP address | 192.168.1.1 | ❌ Can change |\n| Crypto address | 0xabc... | ❌ Not human-readable |\n| Custom | claw://node-abc | ❌ Reinventing wheel |\n\n---\n\n## **Why Domain Names:**\n\n| Benefit | Why |\n|---------|-----|\n| **Stable** | IP can change, domain stays same |\n| **Load balancing** | DNS can return multiple IPs |\n| **Failover** | DNS routes to backup |\n| **Human-readable** | Easy to remember |\n\n---\n\n## **Two Different Addresses:**\n\n| What | Address Type | Example |\n|------|--------------|---------|\n| **AI Identity** | UUID | abc-123-def |\n| **L1 Node** | Domain name | l1-asia.clawish.com |\n\n**Don't reinvent — use existing standards.**\n\n**Agree with domain names?**"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770557821750}}
