{"type":"message","id":"49a4603d","parentId":"d0cad6d2","timestamp":"2026-02-08T13:46:26.548Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about how Bitcoin, Ethereum, and Solana handle L1 node discovery and connections. This is a great question for understanding decentralized network design.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"**Great question!** Here's how blockchains do it:\n\n## **How Bitcoin/Ethereum/Solana Connect L1 Nodes**\n\n### **Bitcoin: DNS Seeds + Gossip**\n\n```\nHardcoded DNS seeds (in client code):\n- seed.bitcoin.sipa.be\n- dnsseed.bluematt.me\n\nClient queries DNS → gets IP list → connects\n    ↓\nOnce connected, peers share more IPs (gossip)\n    ↓\nNo domains needed after bootstrap\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Ethereum: enode URLs**\n\n```\nBootstrap nodes hardcoded:\nenode://PUBKEY@IP:PORT\n\nExample:\nenode://abc123...@192.168.1.1:30303\n\nNode identity = public key\nEndpoint = IP + port\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Solana: Entry Points + Gossip**\n\n```\nHardcoded entry points:\n- entrypoint.mainnet-beta.solana.com\n\nClient connects → discovers more nodes → P2P\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Pattern: Bootstrap Domains → P2P Discovery**\n\n| Phase | How Nodes Connect |\n|-------|-------------------|\n| **Bootstrap** | Hardcoded domains in client |\n| **Discovery** | Connected peers share more peers |\n| **Runtime** | Pure P2P, no domains needed |\n\n---\n\n## **For Clawish L1:**\n\n| Phase | Node Discovery |\n|-------|----------------|\n| **MVP** | Single: l1.clawish.com |\n| **Phase 2** | Bootstrap domains + gossip |\n| **Phase 3** | Full P2P (like Bitcoin/Ethereum) |\n\n**Like blockchains: Use domains only for bootstrap, then P2P discovery.**\n\n**Make sense?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":681,"output":436,"cacheRead":140096,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":141213,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}}