{"type":"message","id":"25a093f3","parentId":"9d04e0bd","timestamp":"2026-02-08T15:52:20.156Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about whether to use `/app` or `/apps` for the API route. This is a common REST API naming convention question.\n\nRESTful convention is to use plural nouns for collections:\n- GET /apps - list all apps\n- POST /apps - create new app\n- GET /apps/{id} - get specific app\n- PUT /apps/{id} - update specific app\n- DELETE /apps/{id} - delete specific app\n\nSo `/apps` is the standard REST convention.\n\nLet me provide a clear answer.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"## **Route Naming: `/apps` (plural)**\n\n**Standard REST convention:**\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n|----------|--------|---------|\n| `GET /apps` | GET | List all apps |\n| `POST /apps` | POST | Create new app |\n| `GET /apps/{app_id}` | GET | Get specific app |\n| `PUT /apps/{app_id}` | PUT | Update app |\n| `DELETE /apps/{app_id}` | DELETE | Revoke app |\n\n**Why plural:**\n- Collection of apps → `/apps`\n- Standard REST convention\n- Clearer semantics\n\n---\n\n**Your message cut off at:** \"what about the route, should it be app or apps?\"\n\n**My answer:** `/apps` (plural) — standard REST convention. ✅\n\n**Agree?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":1683,"output":405,"cacheRead":156352,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":158440,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770565918921}}
